20Tanvir%20created%20was%20unique%20and%2C%20to%20the%20best%20of%20my%20knowledge%2C%20had%20no%20precedent%20or%20parallel%20anywhere%20in%20India.%20It%20eluded%20categorisation.%20Scholars%20and%20critics%20tried%20to%20explain%20it%20variously%20%E2%80%93%20in%20terms%20of%20the%20Indian%20folk%20tradition%2C%20or%20as%20an%20example%20of%20the%20Brechtian%20epic%20theatre%2C%20or%2C%20sometimes%2C%20even%20in%20terms%20of%20the%20aesthetics%20of%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ENatya%20Shastra%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20fact%2C%20however%2C%20is%20that%2C%20while%20Tanvir%E2%80%99s%20work%2C%20in%20its%20different%20aspects%2C%20might%20have%20showed%20an%20affinity%20with%20them%2C%20it%20did%20not%20follow%20any%20of%20them%20consciously%20or%20in%20its%20entirety.%20They%20came%20into%20his%20work%20through%20his%20village%20actors%20and%20their%20background%20in%20traditional%20folk%20performances.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20folk%20legacy%20was%20a%20cornerstone%20of%20Tanvir%E2%80%99s%20theatre%20practice.%20It%20could%20be%20evidenced%20even%20in%20those%20aspects%20which%20are%20reminiscent%20of%20the%20Brechtian%20style%20and%20technique.%20For%20example%2C%20Tanvir%E2%80%99s%20actors%20demonstrated%20or%20%E2%80%9Cshowed%E2%80%9D%2C%20rather%20than%20became%20emotionally%20one%20with%20the%20roles%20they%20were%20playing.%20This%20is%20similar%20to%20the%20epic%20style%20that%20Brecht%20recommends%20in%20which%20an%20actor%20%E2%80%98performs%E2%80%99%20rather%20than%20%E2%80%98lives%E2%80%99%20(as%20in%20Stanislavski)%20the%20role.%20But%20it%20came%20into%20Tanvir%E2%80%99s%20theatre%20not%20as%20a%20conscious%20imitation%20of%20Brecht%E2%80%99s%20theory%20but%20rather%20as%20part%20of%20the%20repertoire%20of%20skills%20that%20the%20folk%20actor%20had%20inherited%20from%20tradition.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F01120224%2FUntitled-design-11.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F01120224%2FUntitled-design-11.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F01120224%2FUntitled-design-11-300x169.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F01120224%2FUntitled-design-11-1024x576.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-670996%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22675%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ERehearsals%20of%20Habib%20Tanvir%E2%80%99s%20(right)%20%E2%80%98Dekh%20rahen%20hain%20nain%E2%80%99%20at%20his%20residence%20in%20Delhi%20in%20the%20mid-1990s.%20Photo%3A%20Sadanand%20Menon%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20is%20not%20surprising%20because%2C%20in%20developing%20his%20theory%20and%20practice%20of%20epic%20theatre%2C%20Brecht%20too%20had%20drawn%20upon%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3Cspan%3Ethe%20collectivist%20or%20communitarian%20traditions%20of%20pre-bourgeois%20origins.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cb%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20only%20feature%20that%20suggests%20some%20degree%20of%20a%20conscious%20Brechtian%20influence%20is%20the%20use%20of%20songs%20to%20comment%20or%20elucidate%20an%20action%20or%20situation%20and%20not%20as%20autonomous%20musical%20interludes%20as%20in%20the%20folk%20dramatic%20tradition.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20246px)%2085vw%2C%20246px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F01120459%2FScreenshot-2023-09-01-at-12.04.2.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22246%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F01120459%2FScreenshot-2023-09-01-at-12.04.2.png%20777w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F01120459%2FScreenshot-2023-09-01-at-12.04.2-194x300.png%20194w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F01120459%2FScreenshot-2023-09-01-at-12.04.2-663x1024.png%20663w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-670998%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22380%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EAerial%20shot%20of%20the%20rehearsal%20space%20at%20Habib%20Tanvir%E2%80%99s%20residence%20in%20Delhi.%20Photo%3A%20Sadanand%20Menon%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3E%3Ci%3E%E2%80%98I%20have%20never%20run%20after%20folk%20forms%2C%20only%20after%20folk%20actors%E2%80%99%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20writer%20has%20had%20the%20privilege%20of%20watching%20almost%20all%20of%20Tanvir%E2%80%99s%20productions%20and%20seeing%20his%20actors%20on%20and%20off%20stage.%20Drawn%20from%20the%20folk%20performance%20tradition%20of%20Chhattisgarh%20called%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Enacha%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3Ethey%20were%20mostly%20unschooled%20and%20had%20no%20formal%20or%20informal%20experience%20of%20the%20modern%20stage.%20Working%20with%20an%20urban%2C%20professional%20repertory%20company%20was%20an%20absolutely%20new%20experience%20for%20them.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%2C%20once%20they%20got%20used%20to%20it%2C%20they%20were%20incredible.%20I%20do%20not%20know%20of%20any%20other%20theatre%20group%20in%20India%20which%20can%20boast%20of%20such%20a%20galaxy%20of%20superb%2C%20unforgettable%20performers.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ETake%20Fida%20Bai%20who%2C%20when%20Tanvir%20first%20noticed%20her%20during%20a%20month%20long%20nacha%20workshop%20in%20Raipur%20in%201972%2C%20had%20no%20stage%20experience%20other%20than%20singing%20and%20dancing.%20But%20she%20turned%20out%20to%20be%20one%20of%20the%20most%20powerful%20female%20stage%20actors%20of%20post-Independence%20India.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFida%20came%20from%20a%20Dalit%20background%20and%20was%20completely%20illiterate.%20She%20could%20not%20even%20sign%20her%20name.%20She%20had%20begun%20her%20career%20as%20a%20nacha%20artiste.%20Like%20other%20Naya%20Theatre%20artistes%20coming%20from%20the%20Chhattisgarhi%20folk%20theatre%20background%2C%20she%20was%20versatile.%20She%20could%20sing%20and%20dance%20as%20well%20as%20act.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWith%20her%20remarkable%20stage%20presence%2C%20booming%20voice%2C%20and%20histrionic%20skills%2C%20she%20made%20every%20role%20she%20played%20unforgettable.%20Her%20performances%20as%20the%20queen%20in%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ECharandas%20Chor%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20and%20in%20the%20title%20roles%20in%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EBahadur%20Kalarin%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20and%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EShajapur%20ki%20Shantibai%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20(an%20adaptation%20of%20Brecht%E2%80%99s%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EGood%20Person%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E)%20are%20remembered%20to%20this%20day.%20Sadly%2C%20she%20retired%20from%20the%20stage%20too%20soon%20because%2C%20after%20a%20tragic%20incident%2C%20she%20lost%20her%20voice%20and%20could%20no%20longer%20perform.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20984px)%2061vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2045vw%2C%20600px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F01120634%2Fpic-8.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22801%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F01120634%2Fpic-8.jpg%20621w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F01120634%2Fpic-8-300x200.jpg%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-670999%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22534%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EHabib%20Tanvir%20and%20Fida%20Bai%20in%20%E2%80%98Bahadur%20Kalarin%E2%80%99.%20Photo%3A%20Nagin%20Tanvir%2FNaya%20Theatre%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EIntertwined%20strands%20of%20traditional%20and%20modern%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAnd%20yet%2C%20for%20all%20its%20involvement%20with%20traditional%20music%2C%20actors%2C%20and%20styles%20of%20performance%2C%20the%20theatre%20that%20Tanvir%20developed%20was%20not%20a%20variety%20of%20%E2%80%98folk%20theatre%E2%80%99.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EUndoubtedly%2C%20in%20his%20theatre%2C%20bodies%2C%20voices%2C%20movements%20and%20gestures%2C%20skills%20and%20rhythm%2C%20music%20and%20speech%20%E2%80%93%20all%20these%20belonged%20to%20the%20folk%20performers.%20But%2C%20on%20a%20deeper%20level%2C%20the%20practical%20aspects%20of%20staging%20and%20critical%20consciousness%20(characterised%20by%20complexity%20of%20vision%2C%20subtlety%20and%20irony%20in%20articulation%2C%20and%20contemporaneity%20of%20concerns)%20which%20gave%20them%20direction%20and%20form%20came%20from%20Tanvir%E2%80%99s%20modern%20disposition.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20other%20words%2C%20his%20plays%20were%20strongly%20evocative%20of%20folk%20performance%20but%20without%20ever%20pretending%20to%20be%20actually%20it.%20Rather%2C%20they%20were%20examples%20of%20a%20theatre%20which%20was%20simultaneously%20modern%20and%20traditional.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHowever%2C%20these%20two%20dimensions%20of%20Tanvir%E2%80%99s%20work%20are%20not%20two%20separate%20currents%20or%20aspects%20of%20his%20theatre.%20On%20the%20contrary%2C%20they%20are%20closely%20intertwined%20and%20defining%20strands%20in%20the%20vibrant%20artistic%20tapestry%20of%20his%20work.%20He%20combined%20and%20interwove%20them%20into%20a%20style%20of%20theatre%20which%20was%20unique%20in%20the%20sense%20that%20it%20neither%20followed%20the%20European%20model%20nor%20did%20it%20blindly%20copy%20any%20traditional%20Indian%20form.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20for%20the%20forms%20of%20folk%20culture%2C%20Tanvir%E2%80%99s%20approach%20to%20them%20was%20neither%20revivalist%20nor%20antiquarian.%20He%20did%20not%20romanticise%20or%20sentimentalise%20them.%20He%20knew%20quite%20well%20the%20debasement%20that%20the%20traditional%20forms%20had%20suffered%20due%20to%20rapid%20urbanisation%20and%20the%20homogenising%20influence%20of%20films%20and%20TV.%20He%20was%20also%20aware%20of%20the%20severe%20ideological%20limitations%20underlying%20the%20simple%20approach%20to%20issues%20and%20problems%20that%20one%20found%20in%20traditional%20forms%20or%20folk%20culture.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHowever%2C%20this%20did%20not%20prevent%20him%20from%20recognising%20that%20there%20were%20skills%20and%20energies%20that%20still%20existed%20in%20Indian%20folk%20traditions%20which%20could%20be%20drawn%20upon%20to%20forge%20a%20new%2C%20truly%20indigenous%20performance%20idiom.%20So%2C%20what%20he%20did%20was%20to%20bring%20in%20these%20energies%20and%20strengths%20of%20traditional%20performances%20in%20order%20to%20fashion%20an%20artistically%20exciting%20and%20cognitively%20enriching%20theatre%20which%20was%20specifically%20contemporary%20or%20non-traditional%20in%20both%20its%20outlook%20and%20its%20form.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHence%2C%20the%20statement%20earlier%20on%20in%20this%20article%20that%20in%20forging%20his%20unique%20idiom%2C%20Tanvir%20was%20also%2C%20in%20some%20ways%2C%20redefining%20the%20very%20concept%20of%20modernity%2C%20particularly%20in%20relation%20to%20culture.%20He%20had%20grave%20reservations%20about%20the%20post-colonial%20project%20of%20modernity%20which%20tended%20to%20exclude%20from%20the%20focus%20of%20its%20attention%20large%20areas%20and%20large%20sections%20of%20ordinary%20Indians%20who%20lived%20outside%20metropolitan%20centres.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20modernity%2C%20Tanvir%20recognised%2C%20was%20flawed.%20It%20failed%20to%20give%20adequate%20attention%20or%20importance%20to%20India%E2%80%99s%20many%20languages%2C%20cultural%20forms%2C%20traditions%2C%20and%20lifestyles.%20In%20the%20name%20of%20nation%20and%20nationality%2C%20markers%20of%20regional%20identities%20were%20often%20swept%20under%20the%20carpet%20and%20even%20sought%20to%20be%20bulldozed%20into%20one%20homogenous%20entity%20by%20establishing%20large%2C%20monolithic%2C%20centralised%20policies%20and%20%E2%80%9Cnational%E2%80%9D%20institutions%20for%20the%20implementation%20of%20those%20policies.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHowever%2C%20Tanvir%20did%20not%20reject%20modernity%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Eper%20se%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20At%20the%20same%20time%2C%20he%20cherished%20a%20rational%20and%20scientific%20approach%20and%20a%20historical%20perspective%20on%20life%20and%20issues.%20What%20Tanvir%E2%80%99s%20work%20implied%20was%2C%20on%20the%20one%20hand%2C%20a%20more%20sensitive%20and%20more%20imaginative%20approach%20to%20traditions%20and%2C%20on%20the%20other%2C%20a%20more%20inclusive%2C%20just%20and%20equitable%20concept%20of%20modernity.%20It%20is%20this%20complex%20blend%2C%20this%20mutually%20enriching%20partnership%2C%20of%20tradition%20and%20modernity%2C%20that%20defines%20Tanvir%E2%80%99s%20theatre%20and%20gives%20form%20to%20his%20plays.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20the%20connection%20between%20Tanvir%E2%80%99s%20work%20and%20folk%20theatre%20traditions%2C%20particularly%20Chhattisgarh%E2%80%99s%20nacha%2C%20is%20widely%20recognised%2C%20what%20is%20not%20fully%20appreciated%20is%20his%20distinctive%20approach%20to%20the%20%E2%80%9Cfolk%E2%80%9D%20as%20well%20as%20the%20%E2%80%9Cmodern%E2%80%9D%20which%20clearly%20set%20him%20apart%20from%20his%20contemporaries%20and%20made%20his%20work%20so%20memorable.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fauthor%2Fjaved-malick%5C%22%3EJaved%20Malick%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20an%20academic%20and%20well-known%20theatre%20scholar.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693550615000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F01121010%2FUntitled-design-12.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fthe-arts%2Fhabib-tanvir-100-birth-anniversary-theatre%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Over%20a%20long%2C%20momentous%20journey%2C%20the%20iconic%20playwright%20and%20director%20blended%20an%20imaginative%20approach%20to%20folk%20tradition%20and%20an%20inclusive%20concept%20of%20modernity%20to%20establish%20his%20unique%2C%20artistically%20exciting%20and%20enriching%20Naya%20Theatre%2C%20contemporary%20in%20outlook%20and%20form.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Sudan%20refugees%20stranded%20without%20healthcare%20in%20Chad%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693549994000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-103272352%2Cimgsize-1659281.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Frest-of-world%2Fsudan-refugees-stranded-without-healthcare-in-chad%2Farticleshow%2F103271947.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F103271947.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3EHundreds%20of%20thousands%20of%20people%20fleeing%20Sudan's%20war%20have%20crossed%20into%20Chad%20to%20find%20themselves%20in%20overcrowded%20camps%2C%20sweltering%20in%20plastic%20huts%20and%20awaiting%20healthcare%20that%20never%20comes.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3