ted%20young%20badminton%20player%20is%20cut%20short%20by%20a%20conspiracy.%20Angry%20and%20bitter%2C%20he%20turns%20his%20back%20on%20the%20game%20he%20loves.%20%3Ci%3ELove-All%3C%2Fi%3E%2C%20a%20sports%20drama%20written%20and%20directed%20by%20Sudhanshu%20Sharma%2C%20begins%20with%20the%20death%20of%20one%20dream%20and%20then%2C%20expectedly%2C%20trains%20the%20spotlight%20on%20the%20birth%20of%20another.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20two%20dreams%20are%20separated%20by%20two%20decades.%20The%20man%20who%20vows%20never%20to%20play%20again%20is%20transferred%20to%20the%20railway%20colony%20in%20Bhopal%20where%20he%20learnt%20the%20ropes%20of%20the%20game.%20With%20him%20are%20his%20wife%2C%20a%20school-going%20son%20(the%20focal%20point%20of%20an%20incipient%20pursuit%20that%20forms%20the%20crux%20of%20the%20film)%20and%20a%20suitcase%20containing%20a%20badminton%20racquet%20that%20has%20seen%20better%20days.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20might%20at%20first%20flush%20seem%20to%20be%20a%20minor%20variation%20on%20a%20triumph-of-the-underdog%20drama%2C%20but%20Love-All%20does%20not%20deviate%20from%20a%20time-worn%20narrative%20template.%20Unbeknownst%20to%20his%20father%2C%20a%20boy%20strays%20into%20badminton%20because%20playing%20a%20sport%20is%20compulsory%20in%20his%20new%20school.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20takes%20to%20the%20game%20like%20a%20fish%20to%20water%20but%20must%20reckon%20with%20a%20series%20of%20obstacles%20-%20the%20first%20and%20foremost%20being%20his%20father's%20dispiriting%20lack%20of%20enthusiasm%20for%20sport%20in%20general%20-%20in%20order%20to%20make%20headway%20on%20the%20badminton%20court.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELove-All%20is%20toplined%20by%20Kay%20Kay%20Menon%2C%20who%20delivers%20a%20consciously%20low-voltage%20performance%20as%20Siddharth%20Sharma%2C%20the%20grown-up%2C%20crusty%20version%20of%20a%20gifted%20boy%20driven%20out%20of%20badminton%20by%20a%20powerful%20clique%20and%20forced%20to%20accept%20a%20menial%20job%20in%20the%20railways.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETwenty%20years%20later%2C%20his%20son%2C%20Aaditya%20(Ark%20Jain)%2C%20gravitates%20towards%20the%20sport%20egged%20on%20by%20his%20mother%2C%20Jaya%20(Shriswara%20Dubey)%2C%20schoolteacher%20Soma%20(Swastika%20Mukherjee)%2C%20one%20half%20of%20an%20abortive%20love%20story%20from%20years%20past%2C%20and%20an%20old%20pal%20of%20his%20father's%2C%20Vijendra%20(Sumit%20Arora)%2C%20who%20owns%20a%20sports%20goods%20shop.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESeveral%20real-life%20badminton%20players%20have%20significant%20onscreen%20roles%20in%20Love-All.%20Their%20presence%20lends%20authenticity%20to%20the%20sporting%20action%20that%20the%20film%20stages%20in%20service%20of%20an%20otherwise%20facile%20drama%20about%20the%20struggles%20of%20a%20young%20prodigy%20in%20the%20face%20of%20great%20adversity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20underlining%20the%20sweat%20and%20blood%20that%20go%20into%20the%20task%20of%20attaining%20excellence%20in%20any%20sport%2C%20the%20story%20plays%20out%20on%20predictable%20lines%2C%20harping%20upon%20cliches%20about%20life%20and%20dreams.%20Most%20sports%20films%20begin%20when%20the%20protagonist%20is%20down%20for%20the%20count%20and%20end%20with%20a%20glorious%20comeback.%20Love-All%20is%20no%20different.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20middle-class%20boy%20is%20pitted%20against%20a%20cocky%20rival%20from%20a%20privileged%20background%2C%20Shourya%20(Kabir%20Verma)%2C%20who%20has%20the%20blessings%20of%20the%20head%20of%20the%20local%20badminton%20association%2C%20Jay%20Pratap%20Singh%20(Raja%20Bundela).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20mandarin%20is%20Shourya's%20grandfather.%20He%20is%20also%20the%20badminton%20official%20who%20scuttled%20the%20career%20of%20Siddharth%20Sharma%20(played%20as%20a%20young%20boy%20by%20Deep%20Rambhiya).%20So%2C%20what%20pans%20out%20in%20the%20next%2090%20minutes%20or%20so%20is%20an%20account%20of%20a%20man%20wronged%20settling%20scores%20by%20backing%20his%20son%20to%20the%20hilt.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%20is%20all%20there%20is%20to%20Love-All.%20Is%20it%20enough%3F%20Perhaps%20not.%20When%20Siddharth%20returns%20to%20Bhopal%2C%20Pandeyji%20(Atul%20Shrivastava)%2C%20the%20man%20next%20door%2C%20says%20casually%20that%20he%20is%20relieved%20and%20happy%20that%20his%20new%20neighbour%20is%2C%20like%20him%2C%20a%20Brahmin.%20Siddharth%20does%20not%20react%20to%20the%20observation%20either%20in%20that%20instant%20or%20anytime%20later.%20Does%20he%20approve%20of%20Pandeyji's%20narrow-mindedness%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELove-All%20does%20not%20clear%20that%20doubt%20nor%20does%20it%20in%20any%20way%20seek%20to%20probe%20the%20country's%20social%20fault%20lines.%20Yes%2C%20there%20is%20in%20here%20a%20man%20named%20Ansari%20(Robin%20Das)%20in%20the%20guise%20of%20an%20avuncular%20and%20supportive%20caretaker%20of%20the%20old%20badminton%20stadium%20to%20which%20a%20young%20Siddharth%20had%20free%20access%20after%20school%20hours.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20scene%20late%20in%20the%20film%2C%20Pandeyji%2C%20the%20caste-conscious%20railwayman%2C%20hugs%20Ansari%20in%20the%20spectators'%20gallery%20when%20Aaditya%20earns%20a%20crucial%20point.%20The%20image%20flashes%20by%20without%20any%20special%20emphasis%20being%20placed%20on%20it.%20At%20no%20point%20does%20Love-All%20have%20anything%20expressly%20to%20say%20about%20the%20unifying%20power%20of%20sport.%20And%20that%20is%20a%20missed%20opportunity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20another%20point%2C%20Siddharth's%20ex-flame%20asserts%20the%20ennobling%20potential%20of%20sports.%20When%20you%20play%20a%20sport%2C%20you%20become%20a%20better%20human%20being%2C%20she%20says.%20But%20given%20the%20kind%20of%20sourpuss%20he%20is%2C%20Siddharth%20belies%20that%20assertion.%20To%20be%20sure%2C%20he%20has%20a%20change%20of%20heart%20in%20the%20nick%20of%20time%20to%20propel%20the%20story%20forward.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20second%20half%20of%20Love-All%20is%20longer%20than%20the%20first%20by%2020%20minutes%20and%20a%20bit.%20The%20extended%20time%20is%20devoted%20to%20a%20series%20of%20matches%20played%20as%20part%20of%20a%20sub-junior%20national%20tournament%20in%20which%20Shourya%2C%20the%20No.%201%2C%20and%20Aaditya%2C%20a%20wild%20card%2C%20battle%20to%20stay%20alive%20in%20the%20championship.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20commentary%20that%20accompanies%20the%20games%20are%20more%20distracting%20than%20helpful.%20It%20makes%20one%20wonder%20if%20there%20is%20a%20way%20the%20makers%20of%20Indian%20sports%20films%20can%20ever%20devise%20a%20narrative%20device%20that%20would%20do%20away%20with%20the%20need%20for%20the%20kind%20of%20hackneyed%2C%20intrusive%20and%20rudimentary%20chatter%20that%20is%20passed%20off%20as%20description%20of%20the%20action%20unfolding%20on%20the%20screen.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMercifully%2C%20with%20the%20youngsters%20in%20the%20film%20being%20actual%20shuttlers%2C%20the%20dynamics%20of%20the%20sport%20we%20see%20on%20the%20screen%20are%20never%20in%20danger%20of%20hitting%20false%20notes.%20That%20is%20the%20film's%20key%20strength%20-%20when%20the%20attention%20is%20on%20badminton%2C%20it%20is%20squarely%20on%20badminton.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20passage%20that%20paves%20the%20way%20for%20the%20climax%2C%20a%20crisis%20is%20engineered%20in%20a%20contrived%20manner%20that%20takes%20away%20from%20the%20'realism'%20of%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20scenes%20on%20the%20court%20and%20on%20the%20sidelines.%20But%20it%20sparks%20a%20confrontation%20that%20puts%20the%20shuttlecock%20in%20the%20politician's%20court%20and%20calls%20out%20the%20myopic%2C%20self-serving%20methods%20that%20men%20of%20his%20ilk%20use%20to%20retain%20control%20over%20the%20sport's%20resources.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2FIleX8QX5Uyw%3Fsi%3DH2J3gIaIih79BAiu%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22315%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20courtside%20slanging%20match%20bet