20government%20complied%2C%20without%20any%20public%20consultation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20on%20the%20global%20stage%20India%20%E2%80%93%20and%20the%20Modi%20government%20%E2%80%93%20claim%20to%20be%20on%20board%20with%20the%20focus%20on%20more%20rigid%20environmental%20laws%2C%20given%20the%20realities%20of%20climate%20change%2C%20the%20facts%20brought%20out%20by%20this%20report%20paint%20a%20different%20picture.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Organized%20Crime%20and%20Corruption%20Reporting%20Project%20(OCCRP)%20has%20found%20that%20among%20other%20changes%2C%20Vedanta%20was%20leading%20the%20way%20in%20pushing%20the%20government%20to%20allow%20mining%20companies%20to%20produce%20up%20to%2050%25%20more%20without%20requiring%20new%20environmental%20approvals.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20push%2C%20according%20to%20the%20OCCRP%2C%20began%20in%202021%20when%20Vedanta%20Resources%20Ltd%20chairman%20Anil%20Agarwal%20wrote%20to%20environment%20minister%20Prakash%20Javadekar%2C%20saying%20making%20these%20changes%20would%20add%20%E2%80%9Cimpetus%E2%80%9D%20to%20India%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%9Crapid%E2%80%9D%20economic%20recovery%20after%20the%20pandemic-related%20slowdown.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CApart%20from%20immediately%20boosting%20production%20and%20economic%20growth%2C%20this%20will%20generate%20huge%20revenue%20for%20the%20Government%20and%20create%20massive%20jobs%2C%E2%80%9D%20Agarwal%20reportedly%20said%20in%20his%20letter.%20He%20also%20said%20that%20allowing%20companies%20to%20produce%2050%25%20more%20without%20applying%20for%20further%20environmental%20clearance%20could%20be%20done%20through%20%E2%80%9Ca%20simple%20notification%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJavadekar%2C%20according%20to%20the%20report%2C%20marked%20this%20letter%20%E2%80%9CVIMP%E2%80%9D%20or%20very%20important%2C%20and%20told%20the%20secretary%20of%20his%20ministry%20and%20the%20director%20general%20of%20forestry%20to%20%E2%80%9Cdiscuss%20%5Bthe%5D%20policy%20issue%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20Agarwal%E2%80%99s%20letter%20to%20Javadekar%2C%20Vedanta%E2%80%99s%20chief%20executive%20Sunil%20Duggal%20wrote%20directly%20to%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%2C%20saying%20he%20could%20%E2%80%9Cboost%20the%20economic%20engine%20immediately%E2%80%9D%20by%20doing%20away%20with%20the%20existing%20environmental%20clearance%20model.%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20office%20forwarded%20this%20letter%20to%20the%20environment%20secretary.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20proposal%20was%20met%20with%20some%20internal%20opposition%2C%20OCCRP%20reports.%20%E2%80%9CMinutes%20from%20one%20meeting%20in%20July%20show%20officials%20feared%20loosening%20the%20rules%20would%20break%20the%20law%2C%20and%20give%20a%20free%20pass%20to%20unrestrained%20mining%20in%20ecologically%20sensitive%20areas.%20A%20summary%20of%20an%20internal%20meeting%20by%20the%20Joint%20Expert%20Appraisal%20Committee%20%E2%80%94%20made%20up%20of%20ministry%20officials%20and%20mining%20experts%20%E2%80%94%20noted%20similar%20concerns%2C%20and%20said%20any%20increase%20in%20mining%20production%20should%20require%20some%20form%20of%20public%20consultation%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20report%20states.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20early%202022%2C%20the%20changes%20Agarwal%20had%20asked%20for%20would%20become%20a%20reality.%20%E2%80%9CThough%20the%20head%20of%20a%20major%20industry%20lobby%20group%20and%20India%E2%80%99s%20mining%20secretary%20also%20pressed%20for%20the%20rules%20to%20be%20loosened%2C%20internal%20documents%20and%20government%20sources%20suggest%20Vedanta%E2%80%99s%20lobbying%20was%20key.%20The%20environment%20ministry%20then%20changed%20the%20regulations%20by%20publishing%20an%20office%20memo%20%E2%80%94%20meant%20to%20be%20used%20for%20inter-office%20communication%20%E2%80%94%20on%20its%20website%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20OCCRP%20states.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CExperts%20say%20this%20type%20of%20backroom%20lobbying%20allows%20powerful%20people%20close%20to%20India%E2%80%99s%20government%20to%20shape%20policies%20in%20their%20favor%2C%20even%20if%20they%20hurt%20local%20communities%20and%20the%20environment.%20By%20modifying%20important%20regulations%20using%20instruments%20like%20office%20memos%2C%20without%20any%20public%20debate%2C%20the%20government%20may%20also%20have%20skirted%20the%20law%2C%20according%20to%20a%20study%20of%20pandemic-era%20regulatory%20changes%20by%20the%20Vidhi%20Centre%20for%20Legal%20Policy%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20report%20continues.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOCCRP%20reports%20that%20it%20obtained%20thousands%20of%20documents%20through%20RTI%20requests%2C%20which%20%E2%80%9Cshow%20government%20officials%20tailored%20the%20rules%20in%20line%20with%20requests%20made%20by%20the%20industry%2C%20and%20in%20particular%20Vedanta%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20a%20clear%20case%20of%20corporate%20capture%20of%20environmental%20governance%2C%E2%80%9D%20environmental%20lawyer%20Ritwick%20Dutta%20told%20OCCRP.%C2%A0%E2%80%9COver%20the%20last%20few%20years%2C%20it%20is%20clear%20that%20most%20changes%20in%20environmental%20laws%20and%20policies%20have%20been%20largely%20guided%20in%20terms%20of%20the%20economic%20benefit%20it%20would%20bring%20to%20certain%20corporate%20entities%20or%20sectors.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%98Lobbying%E2%80%99%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitical-economy%2Findia-shadow-lobbies-business-electoral-funding%5C%22%3Enot%20recognised%20in%20India%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20so%20there%20are%20no%20regulations%20governing%20this%20particular%20kind%20of%20relationship%20between%20the%20government%20and%20corporate%20houses.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20its%20response%20to%20OCCRP%2C%20Vedanta%20said%20it%20is%20%E2%80%9Cone%20of%20the%20leading%20natural%20resources%20organizations%20in%20India%E2%80%9D%20and%20the%20company%20operated%20%E2%80%9Cwith%20an%20objective%20of%20import%20substitution%20by%20enhancing%20domestic%20production%20in%20a%20sustainable%20manner%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20view%20of%20the%20same%2C%20continuous%20representations%20are%20submitted%20for%20consideration%20to%20the%20Government%20in%20the%20best%20interest%20of%20national%20development%20and%20India%E2%80%99s%20march%20towards%20self-reliance%20in%20natural%20resources%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20company%20spokesperson%20continued.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENeither%20the%20prime%20minister%E2%80%99s%20office%20nor%20the%20current%20or%20former%20environment%20minister%20responded%20to%20OCCRP%E2%80%99s%20requests%20for%20comments.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAgarwal%20has%20been%20a%20vocal%20supporter%20of%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20and%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%2C%20and%20said%20in%20the%20past%20that%20Modi%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.moneycontrol.com%2Fnews%2Ftrends%2Fcurrent-affairs%2Fvedantas-anil-agarwal-india-to-become-5th-country-to-manufacture-semiconductors-9974971.html%5C%22%3Einspires%20him%20and%20his%20decisions%3C%2Fa%3E.%20OCCRP%20writes%20that%20contribution%20reports%20analysed%20by%20the%20group%20show%20that%20two%20Vedanta-linked%20trusts%20alone%20%E2%80%9Cdonated%20%246.16%20million%20to%20the%20party%20%5BBJP%5D%20between%202016%20and%202020%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20connections%20of%20Vedanta%20and%20its%20political%20funding%20run%20deeper.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20Modi%20government%20in%202016%20proposed%20to%20amend%20the%20Foreign%20Contribution%20Regulation%20Act%20(FCRA)%2C%201976%2C%20retrospectively%2C%20it%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fnational%2Ffcra-amendment-in-finance-bill%2Farticle22636668.ece%5C%22%3Ewas%20seen%20as%20a%20move%20to%20benefit%20the%20ruling%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20and%20the%20Congress%3C%2Fa%3E%20held%20guilty%20by%20the%20Delhi%20high%20court%20for%20receiving%20foreign%20funds%20from%20two%20subsidiaries%20of%20Vedanta%2C%20a%20London-based%20mining%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Representation%20of%20the%20People%20Act%20and%20the%20FCRA%20bar%20political%20parties%20from%20receiving%20foreign%20funds%2C%20but%20BJP%20went%20ahead%20to%20make%20an%20exception%20for%20itself%2C%20retrospectively.%20The%20government%20amended%20FCRA%20controversially%2C%20through%20the%20Finance%20Bill%20route%2C%20allowing%20foreign-origin%20companies%20to%20finance%20non-governmental%20organisations%20and%20clearing%20the%20way%20for%20donations%20to%20political%20parties%20by%20changing%20the%20definition%20of%20%E2%80%9Cforeign%20companies%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Delhi%20High%20Court%20in%202014%20had%20held%20both%20the%20BJP%20and%20Congress%20parties%20guilty%20of%20violating%20FCRA%20norms%20for%20accepting%20donations%20from%20Vedanta.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fbjp-congress-fcra-foreign-funds-supreme-court%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported%20on%20November%2030%2C%202016%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0on%20the%20BJP%20and%20Congress%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Findia%2Findia-news-india%2Fforeign-funding-bjp-congress-withdraw-appeals-from-sc%2F%5C%22%3Ewithdrawing%20their%20respective%20appeals%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0in%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20against%20the%20Delhi%20high%20court%20verdict%20that%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fnational%2Fbjp-congress-flouted-foreign-funding-norms-delhi-hc%2Farticle5844269.ece%5C%22%3Eheld%20them%20guilty%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20the%20anger%20amongst%20election%20watchdogs%20and%20activists.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693543872000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F01100423%2FE_eN9tNUYAIT7IK.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fvedanta-successfully-lobbied-indian-govt-to-weaken-environmental-regulations-report%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22OCCRP%20has%20found%20that%20Vedanta%20was%20leading%20the%20way%20in%20pushing%20the%20government%20to%20allow%20mining%20companies%20to%20prod