20during%20training.%20Photo%3A%20Wikimedia%20Commons%2FNATO%20Training%20Mission-Afghanistan%2F%20CC%20BY-SA%202.0.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20American%20military%20invaded%20Afghanistan%20in%202001%2C%20soon%20after%20the%209%2F11%20terror%20attacks%2C%20and%20overthrew%20the%20Taliban%20government.%20After%20that%2C%20the%20United%20States%20installed%20Hamid%20Karzai%20as%20the%20President%20of%20Afghanistan%2C%20followed%20by%20Ashraf%20Ghani%20in%202014.%20America%20spent%20vast%20sums%20of%20money%20on%20state-building%20in%20Afghanistan%20for%20two%20decades.%20The%20goal%20was%20to%20help%20Afghanistan%20transition%20to%20democracy%2C%20build%20institutions%2C%20and%20strengthen%20civil%20society.%20These%20efforts%20were%20a%20colossal%20failure.%20The%20Taliban%20regrouped%20in%20neighbouring%20Pakistan%2C%20repeatedly%20launched%20terror%20attacks%2C%20and%20destabilised%20the%20Afghan%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESuccessive%20Afghan%20administrations%20supported%20by%20the%20United%20States%20were%20mired%20in%20corruption%20and%20nepotism.%20Despite%20massive%20investments%2C%20Afghanistan%20did%20not%20metamorphose%20into%20a%20stable%20democracy.%20Sectarian%20violence%2C%20tribal%20loyalties%2C%20low%20levels%20of%20human%20development%2C%20a%20weak%20civil%20society%2C%20institutional%20infirmities%2C%20and%20the%20absence%20of%20an%20ethos%20of%20tolerance%20and%20inclusion%20all%20conspired%20to%20sabotage%20state-building%20efforts.%20Having%20reached%20a%20dead%20end%2C%20the%20United%20States%20withdrew%20in%202021.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWithout%20a%20viable%2C%20secular%20alternative%2C%20it%20was%20compelled%20to%20negotiate%20with%20the%20Taliban%20and%20facilitate%20its%20ascension%20to%20office.%20America%20had%20come%20a%20full%20circle.%20The%20terrorist%20outfit%20it%20vanquished%20two%20decades%20earlier%20returned%20to%20power.%20American%20intervention%20and%20investments%20made%20little%20difference%20to%20the%20lives%20of%20ordinary%20Afghans.%20Afghanistan%20was%20a%20mortifying%20reminder%20of%20yet%20another%20botched%20attempt%20at%20nation-building%20in%20a%20foreign%20country.%20After%20similar%20debacles%20in%20Cuba%2C%20the%20Dominican%20Republic%2C%20Haiti%2C%20Nicaragua%2C%20Cambodia%2C%20Vietnam%2C%20Iraq%2C%20and%20elsewhere%2C%20America%20had%20not%20learned%20its%20lessons.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20reinstatement%20of%20the%20Taliban%20has%20reignited%20old%20fears%20and%20grim%20prognostications.%20In%20its%20latest%20incarnation%2C%20can%20the%20Taliban%20unite%20Afghans%20and%20provide%20a%20stable%20government%3F%20Have%20years%20of%20wilderness%20mellowed%20its%20cadres%3F%20Can%20it%20ameliorate%20the%20lives%20of%20Afghans%2C%20or%20will%20it%20transport%20them%20to%20the%20Medieval%20Ages%3F%20Most%20important%2C%20now%20that%20the%20Taliban%20has%20assumed%20the%20reins%20of%20power%2C%20how%20should%20the%20world%20engage%20with%20it%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20240px)%2085vw%2C%20240px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F06%2F07131717%2F61XHxuMQyL._SY344_BO1204203200_.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22240%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F06%2F07131717%2F61XHxuMQyL._SY344_BO1204203200_.jpg%20226w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F06%2F07131717%2F61XHxuMQyL._SY344_BO1204203200_-196x300.jpg%20196w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-656955%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22367%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Return%20of%20the%20Taliban%3A%20Afghanistan%20After%20the%20Americans%3C%2Fem%3E%20by%20Hassan%20Abbas.%20Publisher%3A%20Yale%20University%20Press.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20new%20book%2C%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Return%20of%20the%20Taliban%3A%20Afghanistan%20After%20the%20Americans%20Left%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20published%20by%20Yale%20University%20Press%20this%20year%2C%20offers%20a%20nuanced%20analysis%20of%20these%20questions.%20Its%20author%2C%20Hassan%20Abbas%2C%20is%20a%20distinguished%20professor%20of%20international%20relations%20at%20the%20Near%20East%20South%20Asia%20Strategic%20Studies%20Center%2C%20National%20Defense%20University%2C%20in%20Washington%2C%20DC.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAbbas%E2%80%99s%20book%20tracks%20the%20vicissitudes%20of%20the%20Taliban%20through%20three%20phases%3A%20first%2C%20from%20its%20inception%20in%201994%20until%202001%2C%20when%20the%20United%20States%20defeated%20it%3B%20second%2C%20from%202003%20to%202018%2C%20a%20time%20when%20Taliban%20forces%20regrouped%20and%20strategised%20in%20Pakistan%3B%20and%2C%20third%2C%20from%202018%20to%20the%20present%2C%20marking%20the%20advent%20of%20Taliban%203.0.%20Based%20on%20this%20rich%2C%20historically%20informed%20inquiry%2C%20Abbas%20maps%20the%20transition%20of%20the%20Taliban%20from%20an%20insurgent%20group%20to%20a%20political%20party%20at%20the%20helm%20of%20a%20government.%20In%20addition%2C%20he%20delineates%20the%20implications%20of%20the%20second%20coming%20of%20the%20Taliban%20for%20lay%20Afghans.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAbbas%20argues%20that%20the%20Taliban%20is%20not%20a%20monolith%20speaking%20in%20a%20single%20voice.%20It%20comprises%20five%20major%20groups%3A%20rigid%20hardliners%2C%20moderates%2C%20foot%20soldiers%2C%20organised%20criminal%20gangs%2C%20and%20ordinary%20villagers%20with%20tribal%20alliances.%20Contrary%20to%20popular%20perception%2C%20not%20all%20Afghans%20are%20hardcore%20champions%20of%20Taliban%20values.%20Some%20pose%20as%20Taliban%20cadres%20to%20camouflage%20their%20criminal%20activities%2C%20others%20go%20along%20for%20opportunistic%20reasons%2C%20yet%20others%20cave%20in%2C%20fearing%20reprisals.%20Die-hard%20zealots%2C%20mainly%20the%20old%20guard%2C%20constitute%20just%20a%20sliver%20of%20Taliban%2C%20albeit%20an%20influential%20one.%20They%20are%20at%20odds%20with%20Generation%20Z%20Taliban%20cadres%2C%20who%20tend%20to%20be%20less%20hostile%20to%20the%20West%20and%20have%20greater%20exposure%20to%20the%20world.%20Regardless%2C%20currently%2C%20the%20old%2C%20fanatical%20elements%20call%20the%20shots.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAbbas%20points%20out%20that%20the%20Taliban%20government%20does%20not%20have%20a%20coherent%20philosophy%20of%20governance.%20Its%20leaders%20have%20no%20use%20for%20democracy.%20The%20Taliban%20wishes%20to%20establish%20an%20Islamic%20emirate%20based%20on%20Islamic%20law%2C%20drawing%20heavily%20from%20the%20Hanafi%20school%20of%20Islamic%20jurisprudence.%20It%20claims%20to%20be%20implementing%20God%E2%80%99s%20rule%20in%20Afghanistan%20and%20sees%20itself%20as%20the%20agent%20of%20this%20heavenly%20mandate.%20A%20312-page%20tome%20titled%C2%A0%3Cem%3EAl-Imarah%20Al-Islamiah%20wa%20Nithamaha%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20or%C2%A0%3Cem%3EThe%20Islamic%20Emirate%20and%20its%20System%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20written%20by%20Abdul%20Hakim%20Ishaqzai%2C%20the%20head%20of%20the%20Afghan%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20serves%20as%20the%20constitution%20of%20the%20Taliban%20regime.%20It%20espouses%20a%20dogmatic%2C%20parochial%20interpretation%20of%20Islam%2C%20prioritises%20religious%20education%2C%20and%20thinks%20women%20are%20intellectually%20deficient%20and%20must%20be%20confined%20to%20their%20homes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fpresent-taliban-regime-afghanistan-book-review%5C%22%3EHow%20Does%20the%20Present%20Taliban%20Regime%20in%20Afghanistan%20Differ%20From%20the%20Previous%20One%3F%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWomen%20and%20minorities%20under%20the%20Taliban%20regime%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20tandem%20with%20this%20antediluvian%20worldview%2C%20the%20Taliban%20government%20discriminates%20against%20women.%20It%20has%20not%20given%20them%20any%20key%20position%20in%20government.%20Women%20have%20to%20wear%20the%20burqa%20ideally%2C%20or%20at%20least%20the%20hijab.%20They%20cannot%20travel%20long%20distances%20without%20being%20accompanied%20by%20a%20close%20male%20relative%20like%20a%20husband%2C%20father%2C%20or%20son%20and%20are%20forbidden%20from%20freely%20mixing%20with%20men%20in%20public.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDelineating%20the%20dismal%20circumstances%20of%20girls%20and%20women%2C%20Abbas%20makes%20two%20interesting%20points.%20First%2C%20he%20avers%20that%20though%20there%20is%20nothing%20in%20the%20Islamic%20canon%20against%20female%20education%2C%20the%20Taliban%20routinely%20mixes%20tribal%20norms%20with%20Islam%20and%20legitimises%20its%20retrograde%20policies.%20He%20does%20not%20explore%20why%20Islamic%20theologians%2C%20religious%20leaders%2C%20and%20Islamic%20regimes%20in%20the%20Middle%20East%20and%20elsewhere%20have%20acquiesced%20in%20the%20Taliban%E2%80%99s%20distortion%20of%20their%20faith.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F31165949%2FAfghan_women_in_Kabul-1.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F31165949%2FAfghan_women_in_Kabul-1.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F31165949%2FAfghan_women_in_Kabul-1-300x200.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F31165949%2FAfghan_women_in_Kabul-1-1024x682.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-670888%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22799%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ERepresentational%20image.%20Afghan%20women%20in%20Kabul%20in%20August%202013.%20Photo%3A%20Wikimedia%20Commons%2FNinara%2FCC%20BY%202.0%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESecond%2C%20Abbas%20underscores%20the%20ideological%20tensions%20between%20the%20rigid%20old%20guard%20and%20the%20moderates%20in%20the%20Taliban%20regime%20on%20the%20gender%20question.%20Unlike%20the%20slightly%20liberal%20moderates%2C%20the%20hardliners%20led%20by%20Mullah%20Hibatullah%20Akundzada%2C%20the%20%3Cem%3EAmeer%20ul-Momineen%3C%2Fem%3E%20or%20the%20supreme%20leader%20of%20the%20Taliban%2C%20based%20in%20Kandahar%20in%20the%20south%2C%20champion%20a%20moth-eaten%20ideology%20implacably%20opposed%20to%20female%20education.%20The%20moderates%20prevailed%20for%20a%20while%20when%20the%20new%20Taliban%20government%20announced%20in%20May%202022%20that%20women%20would%20be%20allowed%20to%20work%20and%20girls%20could%20continue%20schooling.%20This%20victory%20was%20short-lived.%20In%20a%20massive%20setback%20to%20women%2C%20the%20Taliban%20government%20quickly%20rescinded%20its%20decision.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwomen%2Fwill-raise-voice-against-injustice-a-year-after-talibans-return-some-women-fight-for-freedom%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98Will%20Raise%20Voice%20Against%20Injustice%E2%80%99%3A%20A%20Year%20After%20Taliban%E2%80%99s%20Return%2C%20Some%20Women%20Fight%20for%20Freedom%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20maltreatment%20of%20religious%20minorities%2C%20mainly%20the%20Shia%20Hazaras%2C%20and%20the%20anti-Shia%20sectarianism%20in%20the%20countryside%20are%20the%20other%20major%20challenges%20the%20Taliban%20has%20to%20address.%20Abbas%20offers%20a%20chilling%20account%20of%20the%20genocide%20of%20Hazaras%20at%20the%20hands%20of%20the%20Taliban.%20Hazaras%20have%20endured%20unprecedented%20human%20rights%20violations%2C%20which%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20world%20seems%20to%20have%20completely%20ignored.%20Taliban%20cadres%20have%20forcibly%20dislocated%20the%20Hazaras%2C%20bombed%20their%20mosques%20and%20religious%20processions%2C%20alienated%20them%20from%20their%20lands%2C%20and%20denied%20them%20humanitarian%20aid.%C2%A0Hazara%20women%20have%20borne%20the%20brunt%20of%20Taliban%20brutalities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Abbas%2C%20the%20Taliban%20detests%20the%20Hazaras%20as%20they%20are%20successful%20in%20business%2C%20progressive%2C%20and%20pro-democracy.%20It%20has%20wholly%20sidelined%20them%20from%20the%20government.%20The%2033-member%2C%20all-men%20%E2%80%98caretaker%E2%80%99%20cabinet%20appointed%20soon%20after%20the%20Taliban%20returned%20to%20power%20comprised%2030%20Pashtuns%2C%20two%20Tajiks%2C%20and%20one%20Uzbek.%20Women%20and%20Hazaras%20were%20excluded.%20To%20whitewash%20its%20egregious%20discrimination%2C%20the%20Taliban%20government%20has%20promised%20to%20help%20Hazaras%2C%20a%20claim%20with%20few%20takers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%20to%20the%20vexed%20question%20of%20women%20and%20minorities%2C%20Abbas%20argues%20that%20the%20Taliban%20government%20has%20to%20quell%20factionalism%20within%20its%20ranks%20and%20neutralise%20terror%20groups%20such%20as%20the%20Tehrik-e-Taliban%20Pakistan%20(TTP)%20and%20the%20Islamic%20State%20of%20Khorasan%20(ISK).%20Internally%2C%20the%20Taliban%20is%20riven%20by%20internecine%20factions%20with%20divided%20loyalties%20and%20colliding%20visions%20for%20Afghanistan.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20crucial%20issues%20such%20as%20the%20abuse%20of%20women%20and%20minorities%2C%20the%20Taliban%E2%80%99s%20engagement%20with%20its%20neighbours%2C%20and%20its%20acceptance%20of%20Western%20culture%2C%20they%20differ%20vastly.%20While%20the%20younger%2C%20moderate%20groups%20are%20more%20accepting%20of%20modernity%2C%20the%20older%2C%20radical%20factions%20remain%20hidebound.%20Recurrent%20bouts%20of%20colonialism%20and%20foreign%20domination%20have%20made%20them%20paranoid%20about%20outside%20influences.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EFactionalism%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAbbas%20maintains%20that%20if%20managing%20the%20internal%20contradictions%20is%20arduous%2C%20containing%20terror%20groups%20is%20virtually%20impossible%20as%20they%20batten%20on%20cross-border%20patronage.%20Thus%2C%20the%20ISK%20%E2%80%93%20the%20progeny%20of%20the%20dreaded%20Islamic%20State%20of%20Iraq%20and%20Syria%2C%20a%20jihadist%20Salafi%20movement%20aiming%20to%20establish%20an%20Islamic%20caliphate%20%E2%80%93%20is%20an%20implacable%20group%20responsible%20for%20262%20terrorist%20acts%20between%20August%202021%20and%20August%202022.%20It%20views%20the%20Taliban%20leaders%20as%20traitors%20for%20entering%20into%20an%20agreement%20with%20the%20United%20States%20and%20has%20vowed%20to%20dislodge%20the%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESimilarly%2C%20the%20Pakistan-sponsored%20TTP%20has%20wreaked%20havoc%20in%20Afghanistan%20through%20ghastly%20terror%20attacks.%20Pakistan%20has%20propped%20up%20the%20TTP%20to%20strengthen%20its%20foothold%20in%20Afghanistan%20and%20to%20outsmart%20its%20old%20rival%2C%20India.%20Fearing%20increasing%20Indian%20influence%20on%20the%20Taliban%2C%20Pakistan%20wishes%20to%20destabilise%20the%20Afghan%20Taliban.%20An%20ardent%20advocate%20of%20a%20hardline%20approach%2C%20the%20TTP%20has%20actively%20collaborated%20with%20the%20ISK%20to%20create%20violence%20and%20political%20instability%20in%20Afghanistan.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFlailing%20to%20control%20these%20extremist%20groups%20and%20apprehensive%20of%20their%20combined%20strength%2C%20the%20Taliban%20government%20worries%20it%20could%20be%20overrun%20if%20seen%20as%20diluting%20its%20core%20ideology.%20Abbas%20posits%20that%20it%20is%20crucial%20to%20appreciate%20these%20agonising%20compulsions%20of%20the%20Taliban%20regime.%20Disregarding%20them%20will%20isolate%20the%20Taliban%20and%20diminish%20its%20capacity%20to%20contain%20militancy%2C%20hurtling%20Afghanistan%20into%20another%20prolonged%20period%20of%20chaos%20and%20violence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAbbas%20appositely%20emphasises%20that%20these%20complications%20are%20exacerbated%20by%20a%20massive%20financial%20crisis%20that%20has%20pushed%20millions%20into%20desperate%20lives%20of%20immiseration.%20Twenty%20million%20Afghans%20are%20currently%20facing%20chronic%20food%20shortages.%203.2%20million%20children%20suffered%20malnutrition%20in%202022.%20The%20Afghan%20economy%20has%20shrunk%20by%2020%25%20to%2030%25%20since%202021%20after%20the%20American%20financial%20support%20ended.%20Before%20the%20second%20coming%20of%20the%20Taliban%2C%20the%20Ashraf%20Ghani%20administration%20was%20functioning%20with%20a%20foreign-funded%20annual%20budget%20of%20%24%208%20billion.%20Now%2C%20bereft%20of%20foreign%20aid%2C%20the%20Afghan%20budget%20has%20shrunk%20to%20%242.6%20billion%20with%20a%20projected%20deficit%20of%20%24%20500%20million.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDecades%20of%20chronic%20political%20instability%2C%20social%20cleavages%2C%20and%20foreign%20interference%20in%20domestic%20matters%20have%20engendered%20insuperable%20problems%20of%20governance.%20Abbas%20identifies%20the%20five%20areas%20of%20concern%20for%20the%20Taliban%3A%20the%20paucity%20of%20economic%20resources%2C%20eroding%20legitimacy%20and%20acceptance%20by%20its%20people%2C%20recognition%20by%20the%20international%20community%2C%20attracting%20qualified%20people%2C%20and%20accommodating%20rival%20factions%20in%20government.%20Though%20pressing%2C%20these%20needs%20are%20overshadowed%20by%20abysmal%20human%20development%20indices%20and%20the%20absence%20of%20meaningful%20initiatives%20for%20fostering%20human%20capabilities%2C%20a%20critical%20issue%20the%20author%20unfortunately%20overlooks.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ETaliban%E2%80%99s%20engagement%20with%20the%20world%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThough%20doomed%20to%20die%2C%20Afghanistan%20seems%20determined%20to%20survive.%20Abbas%20reposes%20his%20faith%20in%20the%20long%20tradition%20of%20Sufism%2C%20tolerance%2C%20pluralism%2C%20and%20mysticism%20in%20Afghanistan%20and%20posits%20that%20its%20centuries-old%20culture%20will%20prevail.%20In%20the%20interim%2C%20he%20urges%20the%20global%20community%20to%20engage%20with%20the%20Taliban%20and%20continue%20to%20support%20its%20initiatives%20to%20rebuild%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20all%20its%20poverty%2C%20Afghanistan%20%E2%80%93%20about%20one-fifth%20the%20size%20of%20India%20with%20a%20population%20of%2041%20million%20people%20%E2%80%93%20is%20a%20staggeringly%20rich%20country%20in%20terms%20of%20its%20natural%20resources.%20It%20sits%20on%20an%20estimated%20three%20trillion-dollar%20mineral%20reserves%20in%20Mes%20Aynak%20copper%20mines.%20In%20addition%2C%20it%20has%20enormous%20deposits%20of%20lithium%2C%20iron%2C%20marble%2C%20talc%2C%20coal%2C%20chromite%2C%20cobalt%2C%20and%20gold.%20Several%20neighbouring%20countries%2C%20drawn%20by%20Afghanistan%E2%80%99s%20abundant%20natural%20resources%20and%20geostrategic%20location%20in%20Central%20Asia%2C%20have%20assisted%20the%20Taliban%20but%20stopped%20short%20of%20recognising%20its%20government.%20Some%20have%20misgivings%20about%20the%20Taliban%E2%80%99s%20ideology%3B%20others%20fear%20regional%20rivalries.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20and%20Pakistan%20wish%20to%20gain%20leverage%20against%20each%20other%20by%20cultivating%20the%20Taliban.%20Abbas%20states%20that%20since%20it%20supported%20the%20Taliban%20and%20Afghan%20refugees%20for%20decades%2C%20Pakistan%20feels%20entitled%20to%20treat%20Afghanistan%20as%20its%20fiefdom.%20Besides%2C%20it%20fears%20that%20the%20Taliban%20government%20might%20veer%20toward%20India%2C%20allowing%20the%20latter%20to%20use%20Afghanistan%20to%20foment%20trouble%20in%20Pakistan.%20India%20understands%20the%20geostrategic%20position%20of%20Afghanistan%20and%20wishes%20to%20promote%20stability%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnder%20its%20%E2%80%98Neighborhood%20First%E2%80%99%20policy%2C%20it%20has%20generously%20funded%20the%20construction%20of%20the%20%24300%20million%20Afghan-India%20Friendship%20dam%20and%20the%20%24%2090%20million%20Afghan%20parliament%20building.%20In%20addition%2C%20India%20provided%20humanitarian%20aid%20during%20the%20Covid-19%20pandemic.%20India%E2%80%99s%20main%20concerns%20are%20security%20along%20its%20border%20and%20countering%20the%20influence%20of%20China%20and%20Pakistan%20in%20the%20region.%20The%20Taliban%20has%20responded%20favourably%20to%20India%E2%80%99s%20security%20concerns.%20Nevertheless%2C%20a%20trust%20deficit%20exists%20as%20India%20is%20uneasy%20about%20the%20strong%20nexus%20between%20Pakistan%20and%20the%20Taliban.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChina%20has%20two%20main%20interests%3A%20Afghan%20economic%20resources%20and%20the%20desire%20to%20combat%20Uyghur%20militancy%20and%20separatism%20through%20the%20Wakhan%20Corridor%2C%20a%20strip%20of%20territory%20connecting%20Xinjiang%20to%20Afghanistan.%20Neighbouring%20Iran%20fears%20the%20anti-Shia%20militancy%20of%20the%20ISK%20and%20wishes%20to%20cultivate%20the%20Taliban%20for%20its%20security.%20Likewise%2C%20Russia%20is%20worried%20about%20regional%20instability%20in%20Central%20Asia%20and%20drug%20trafficking%20from%20Afghanistan.%20Regardless%20of%20their%20diverse%20motivations%2C%20all%20countries%20in%20the%20region%20are%20rooting%20for%20peace%20and%20security%20in%20Afghanistan.%20Cognisant%20of%20global%20expectations%2C%20the%20new%20regime%20is%20trying%20to%20reshape%20its%20anti-Western%2C%20anti-modern%20cadres%20into%20a%20responsible%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAbbas%20exhorts%20the%20world%20community%20to%20quit%20pontificating%20and%20talking%20down%20to%20the%20Taliban.%20Times%20have%20changed%2C%20and%20so%20has%20Afghanistan.%20Mindful%20of%20the%20sensibilities%20of%20the%20younger%20generation%2C%20the%20Taliban%20is%20struggling%20to%20slough%20off%20its%20old%20ideological%20baggage.%20What%20it%20seriously%20needs%20is%20support%2C%20not%20sermons.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Return%20of%20the%20Taliban%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0is%20a%20masterful%20work%20of%20scholarship.%20Replete%20with%20facts%20and%20figures%2C%20rich%20in%20its%20historical%20account%2C%20and%20written%20in%20a%20riveting%20style%2C%20this%20book%20deserves%20serious%20attention.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EBadrinath%20Rao%20is%20an%20Associate%20Professor%20of%20Sociology%20and%20Asian%20Studies%20at%20Kettering%20University%20in%20Flint%2C%20Michigan.%20An%20attorney%20in%20Michigan%2C%20he%20is%20also%20the%20host%20and%20Executive%20Producer%20of%20%E2%80%98Ideas%20and%20Insights%E2%80%99%2C%20a%20public%20affairs%20TV%20show.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693539026000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F31165949%2FAfghan_women_in_Kabul-1.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Freview-a-deep-dive-into-talibans-transition-from-insurgent-group-to-heading-afghan-government%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Hassan%20Abbas's%20latest%20book%20'The%20Return%20of%20the%20Taliban%3A%20Afghanistan%20After%20the%20Americans%20Left'%20covers%20a%20whole%20host%20of%20issues%20concerning%20Taliban%20and%20particularly%20its%20journey%20after%20the%20Americans%20left%20Afghanistan%20in%202021.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Freview-a-deep-dive-into-talibans-transition-from-insurgent-group-to-heading-afghan-government%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22After%20Domestic%20LPG%20Price%20Reduction%2C%20Commercial%20LPG%20Prices%20Cut%20By%20Rs%20158%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20major%20relief%20to%20LPG%20consumers%2C%20Public%20sector%20Oil%20Marketing%20Companies%20(OMCs)%20have%20slashed%20the%20price%20of%2019%20KG%20commercial%20LPG%20gas%20cylinders%20by%20Rs%20158%2C%20according%20to%20the%20sources.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20new%20prices%20will%20be%20effective%20from%20today%20and%20Delhi's%20retail%20sales%20price%20of%2019kg%20commercial%20LPG%20cylinder%20will%20be%20Rs%201%2C522.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEarlier%2C%20on%20the%20eve%20of%20Raksha%20Bandhan%2C%20the%