%3A%22India%20take%20on%20Pakistan%20in%20a%20much-anticipated%20Asia%20Cup%202023%20match%20on%20Saturday.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A60%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fsports.ndtv.com%2Fasia-cup-2023%2Fdont-think-if-any-other-batter-pakistan-stars-big-praise-for-virat-kohli-ahead-of-asia-cup-2023-clash-4346097%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fsports-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fsports.ndtv.com%2Fasia-cup-2023%2Fdont-think-if-any-other-batter-pakistan-stars-big-praise-for-virat-kohli-ahead-of-asia-cup-2023-clash-4346097%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fsports.ndtv.com%2Fasia-cup-2023%2Fdont-think-if-any-other-batter-pakistan-stars-big-praise-for-virat-kohli-ahead-of-asia-cup-2023-clash-4346097%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Indian%20American%20Arrested%20In%20New%20Jersey%20In%20%2413%20Million%20Tech%20Fraud%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EAn%20Indian%20American%20has%20been%20arrested%20in%20New%20Jersey%20on%20charge%20of%20being%20part%20of%20a%20technical%20support%20scam%20that%20targeted%20more%20than%207%2C000%20victims%20defrauding%20them%20of%20more%20than%20USD%2013%20million%2C%20a%20US%20Attorney%20announced%20Thursday.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECharged%20with%20one%20count%20of%20conspiracy%20to%20commit%20wire%20fraud%2C%20Manoj%20Yadav%20appeared%20before%20US%20Magistrate%20Judge%20Jos%C3%A9%20R.%20Almonte%20in%20Newark%20federal%20court.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20defendant%20and%20his%20conspirators%20are%20alleged%20to%20have%20misled%20their%20numerous%20victims%20into%20thinking%20that%20they%20were%20a%20legitimate%20technology%20support%20company%20affiliated%20with%20a%20major%20software%20company%2C%26quot%3B%20US%20Attorney%20Philip%20R%20Sellinger%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20claiming%20to%20provide%20technical%20support%20for%20issues%20involving%20the%20software%20company's%20popular%20accounting%20software%2C%20they%20allegedly%20charged%20the%20victims%20exorbitant%20fees%20for%20purported%20support%20services%20that%20were%20not%20authorized%20by%20the%20software%20company%2C%20he%20alleged.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20allege%20Yadav%20lied%20to%20software%20users%20and%20forced%20them%20to%20pay%20for%20services%20that%20would%20usually%20come%20free%20with%20their%20initial%20purchase%2C%26quot%3B%20FBI%20Special%20Agent%20in%20Charge%20James%20E%20Dennehy%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20count%20of%20conspiracy%20to%20commit%20wire%20fraud%20carries%20a%20maximum%20penalty%20of%2020%20years%20in%20prison%20and%20a%20fine%20of%20USD%202%2C50%2C000%20or%20twice%20the%20gross%20profit%20or%20loss%20caused%20by%20the%20offense%2C%20whichever%20is%20greatest.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20amount%20he's%20accused%20of%20stealing%20from%20his%20victims%20and%20the%20number%20of%20victims%20seem%20shocking%3B%20however%2C%20we%20are%20seeing%20an%20incredible%20increase%20in%20all%20types%20of%20tech%20support%20scams.%20The%20fraudsters%20are%20pretty%20savvy%20in%20how%20they%20con%20money%20out%20of%20people%2C%20even%20those%20of%20us%20who%20think%20we're%20smart%20enough%20to%20not%20fall%20for%20it.%20If%20you%20think%20you're%20a%20victim%2C%20please%20reach%20out%20to%20the%20FBI%2C%E2%80%9D%20Dennehy%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20federal%20prosecutors%2C%20from%202017%20through%202023%2C%20Yadav%20and%20his%20conspirators%2C%20many%20of%20whom%20were%20in%20India%2C%20fraudulently%20held%20themselves%20out%20as%20a%20technology%20support%20company%20affiliated%20with%20a%20major%20US%20business%20and%20accounting%20software%20company%20that%20developed%20and%20sold%20a%20widely%20used%20accounting%20software%20product.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20operated%20under%20multiple%20fraudulent%20business%20names%2C%20including%20%E2%80%9CPhebs%20Software%20Services%2C%20LLC%2C%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%9CPhebs%20Software%20Services%2C%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%9CPN%20Bookkeeping%20Services%2C%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%9CPhebbs%20Consulting%2C%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%9CQuickbooks%20Tech%20Assist%2C%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%9CQuickbook%20US%2C%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%9CQuickbooks%20Accounting%2C%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9CQuickbooks%20Support%20Team.%E2%80%9D%20According%20to%20court%20documents%2C%20the%20conspirators%20would%20contact%20victims%20under%20the%20guise%20of%20fixing%20technical%20issues%20they%20faced%20with%20the%20accounting%20software.%20After%20receiving%20tech%20support%20from%20the%20conspirators%20under%20these%20fraudulent%20pretenses%2C%20the%20victims%20would%20either%20be%20charged%20exorbitant%20fees%20or%20additional%20subscription%20fees.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20%E2%80%9Cservices%E2%80%9D%20were%20all%20fraudulent%3A%20They%20would%20not%20cost%20any%20additional%20money%20for%20customers%20who%20contacted%20the%20actual%20software%20company%2C%20and%20the%20software%20company%20never%20authorized%20Yadav%20or%20his%20conspirators%20to%20act%20on%20its%20behalf%20or%20charge%20any%20fees.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYadav%20personally%20participated%20in%20the%20scheme%20by%20charging%20the%20victims%20for%20the%20fraudulent%20technology%20support%20services%20and%20funnelling%20millions%20of%20dollars%20from%20these%20victims%20to%20his%20conspirators%2C%20it%20alleged%2C%20adding%20that%20he%20fraudulently%20obtained%20these%20funds%20through%20the%20Phebs%20Software%20Services%2C%20LLC%2C%20which%20he%20himself%20formed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%20entity%20did%20business%20as%20both%20%E2%80%9CPhebs%20Software%20Services%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9CQuickbooks%20Accounting.%E2%80%9D%20Yadav%20also%20used%20these%20entity%20names%20to%20falsely%20hold%20himself%20out%20to%20banks%20and%20victim%20customers%20as%20an%20accounting%20company%20legitimately%20affiliated%20with%20the%20software%20company.%20He%20did%20this%20to%20prevent%20charge%20backs%2C%20Better%20Business%20Bureau%20complaints%2C%20and%20the%20closure%20of%20bank%20accounts.%20Yadav%20sent%20his%20conspirator