f%20the%20US%20Navy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EThe%20arsenal%20ship%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22840%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22US%20Navy%20arsenal%20ship%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64ef65a06f301e00193e2a48%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22629%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAn%20illustration%20of%20a%20possible%20arsenal%20ship%20published%20in%20the%20US%20Navy's%20All%20Hands%20magazine%20in%20May%201995.%3Cp%3EUS%20Navy%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EProposed%20in%201996%2C%20the%20arsenal%20ship%20was%20one%20of%20the%20US%20Navy's%20first%20proposed%20adaptations%20to%20the%20post-Cold%20War%20threat%20environment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20the%20Soviet%20Union%20gone%20and%20the%20Russian%20Navy%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgaleotti-putins-wars-how-russia-rebuilt-and-destroyed-its-military-2023-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20shell%20of%20its%20forbear's%20strength%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20there%20was%20little%20need%20for%20a%20large%20fleet%20dedicated%20to%20battling%20a%20first-rate%20adversary%20on%20the%20high%20seas.%20Instead%2C%20most%20threats%20were%20ground-based%20and%20either%20close%20to%20shore%20or%20farther%20inland.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EConsequently%2C%20the%20US%20Navy%20reduced%20the%20number%20of%20ships%20in%20its%20inventory%20and%20focused%20on%20developing%20long-range%20strike%20capability%20for%20use%20in%20joint%20operations%20with%20other%20military%20branches.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20maximize%20its%20role%20in%20this%20new%20era%2C%20the%20Navy%20proposed%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fman.fas.org%2Fdod-101%2Fsys%2Fship%2Fdocs%2Frsnlship.htm%23Costs%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecompletely%20new%20type%20of%20warship%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%20A%20massive%2C%20stealthy%2C%20highly%20automated%20vessel%20%E2%80%94%20requiring%20a%20crew%20of%20no%20more%20than%2050%20%E2%80%94%20a