C%20Virginia%2C%20on%20Oct.%2010%2C%201991.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64f0f79557bff7001947fe78%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221745%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EClarence%20Thomas%20in%201991.%3Cp%3EBarry%20Thumma%2FAP%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EBillionaire%20Harlan%20Crow%20bought%20Clarence%20Thomas'%20mom's%20house%20%E2%80%94%20which%20the%20justice%20partly%20owned%20%E2%80%94%20in%202014.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThe%20sale%20was%20undisclosed%2C%20raising%20questions%20about%20the%20ethics%20of%20billionaires%20secretly%20doing%20business%20with%20Supreme%20Court%20justices.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThomas'%20lawyers%20now%20say%20the%20secret%20deal%20happened%20in%20part%20because%20of%20the%20terrible%20conditions%20of%20the%20house%20and%20neighborhood.%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EEarlier%20this%20year%2C%20we%20learned%20that%20Supreme%20Court%20Justice%20Clarence%20Thomas%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fclarence-thomas-sold-his-childhood-home-gop-donor-harlan-crow-2023-4%5C%22%3Esecretly%20sold%3C%2Fa%3E%20his%20childhood%20home%2C%20which%20his%20mother%20still%20lives%20in%2C%20to%20billionaire%20Harlan%20Crow%20in%202014.%20The%20justice%20was%20a%20one-third%20owner%20of%20the%20property%20at%20the%20time.%20Despite%20the%20obvious%20ethical%20concerns%20of%20a%20Supreme%20Court%20justice%20doing%20business%20with%20a%20billionaire%2C%20the%20sale%20was%20never%20disclosed%2C%20and%20only%20came%20to%20light%20thanks%20to%20ProPublica's%20reporting.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EToday%2C%20in%20light%20of%20Thomas'%20most%20recent%20financial%20disclosure%2C%20which%2C%20wouldn't%20you%20know%20it%2C%20suddenly%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fharlan-crow-clarence-thomas-new-financial-disclosure-flights-scotus-2023-8%5C%22%3Edetails%20all%20sorts%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20ties%20to%20Crow%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20justice's%20lawyer%20released%20a%20statement%20defending%20the%20home's%20sale.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%202014%2C%20Harlan%20Crow%2C%20a%20longtime%20friend%20of%20Justice%20and%20Mrs.%20Thomas%2C%20visited%20Savannah%20with%20Justice%20Thomas%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.berkefarah.com%2Fnews%2F2023%2F8%2F31%2Felliot-s-berke-releases-statement-on-behalf-of-client-justice-clarence-thomas-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estatement%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20Elliot%20S.%20Berke%20reads.%20%26quot%3BMr.%20Crow%20witnessed%20firsthand%20how%20the%20neighborhood%20was%20blighted%20and%20dangerous%20with%20derelicts%2C%20drug%20users%2C%20and%20junkies%2C%20notably%20in%20the%20house%20next%20to%20the%20Justice's%20mother%20and%20in%20the%20other%20houses%20on%20her%20street.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThomas%20joined%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20in%201991%2C%20meaning%20that%20in%202014%2C%20when%20his%20mother%20was%20still%20living%20in%20a%20neighborhood%20blighted%20and%20dangerous%20with%20derelicts%2C%20drug%20users%2C%20and%20junkies%2C%20he'd%20been%20one%20of%20the%20most%20powerful%20people%20in%20the%20country%20for%20more%20than%2022%20years.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20statement%20went%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMr.%20Crow%20asked%20Justice%20Thomas%20what%20he%20intended%20to%20do%20with%20the%20home%20after%20his%20mother%20(who%20was%20in%20her%2080s%20at%20the%20time)%20passed%20away%2C%20and%20the%20Justice%20replied%20that%20he%20intended%20to%20have%20the%20property%20bulldozed%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20reads.%20%26quot%3BMr.%20Crow%20indicated%20he%20wanted%20to%20preserve%20the%20home%20for%20a%20possible%20museum%20and%20asked%20his%20team%20to%20review%20the%20idea%20of%20doing%20so.%20When%20he%20first%20raised%20the%20idea%20of%20purchasing%20this%20home%20to%20preserve%20it%2C%20Mr.%20Crow%20did%20not%20know%20that%20Justice%20Thomas%20had%20a%201%2F3%20interest%2