published%20in%20the%20journal%20Environmental%20Science%20%26amp%3B%20Technology.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20researchers%20tested%20boar%20meat%20for%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-honey-has-traces-of-fallout-from-50s60s-nuke-testing-2021-4%5C%22%3Eradioactive%20isotope%20cesium-137%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20fission%20product.%20Cesium-137%20has%20a%2030-year%20half-life%20%E2%80%94%20the%20time%20it%20takes%20for%20the%20radioactive%20material%20to%20decay%20by%20half.%20But%20in%20some%20locations%2C%20boars'%20cesium-137%20levels%20were%20staying%20about%20the%20same.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20researchers%20found%20boar-meat%20contamination%20linked%20to%20atmospheric%20weapons%20from%20the%201950s%20and%20'60s.%20The%20isotopes%20from%20the%20weapons%20and%20Chernobyl%20interacting%20may%20be%20the%20cause%2C%20one%20of%20the%20study's%20authors%2C%20Bin%20Feng%2C%20told%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.vice.com%2Fen%2Farticle%2Fak3jbz%2Fnuclear-weapons-turned-wild-boars-into-an-irradiated-menace-study-finds%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20Vice%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20sources%20mixed%20together%2C%20and%20became%20a%20new%20source%20that%20can%20get%20stronger%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BThis%20is%20the%20reason%2C%20we%20think%2C%20why%20the%20cesium%20contamination%20is%20so%20strong%20and%20persistent.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20wild%20boar%20paradox%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%201986%2C%20an%20explosion%20at%20the%20Chernobyl%20Nuclear%20Power%20Plant%20in%20Ukraine%20killed%20two%20people%20immediately%20and%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fslate.com%2Ftechnology%2F2013%2F04%2Fchernobyl-death-toll-how-many-cancer-cases-are-caused-by-low-level-radiation.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20thousands%20more%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20radiation%20poisoning%20and%20radioactive%20fallout%20after.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnuclear-bomb-attack-russia-ukraine-how-strong-far-2022-2%5C%22%3Efallout%20spread%20for%20hundreds%20of%20miles%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20including%20to%20Bavaria%20in%20southeastern%20Germany%2C%20depositing%20radioactive%20material%20into%20the%20soil%20and%20the%20forest%20animals%20that%20lived%20there.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20forest%20animals%20in%20the%20area%20showed%20high%20levels%20of%20radioactive%20cesium%20after%20the%20accident.%20Over%20time%2C%20rainfall%20and%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.eurekalert.org%2Fnews-releases%2F1000093%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20other%20effects%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20in%20addition%20to%20nuclear%20decay%2C%20lessened%20the%20amount%20of%20cesium%20the%20animals%20and%20plants%20absorbed.%20Contamination%20in%20many%20species%20declined.%20But%20not%20in%20the%20wild%20boars.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.popsci.com%2Farticle%2Fscience%2Fgerman-boars-are-too-radioactive-eat%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20prized%20for%20their%20meat%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20many%20German%20boars%20are%20too%20radioactive%20to%20eat%2C%20generations%20later.%20Hunters%20must%20have%20any%20boars%20they%20kill%20tested%20for%20radioactivity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202014%2C%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.telegraph.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworldnews%2Feurope%2Fgermany%2F11068298%2FRadioactive-wild-boar-roaming-the-forests-of-Germany.html%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20The%20Telegraph%3C%2Fa%3E%20reported%20that%20roughly%20one%20in%20three%20exceeded%20regulatory%20levels.%20The%20new%20study%20found%2088%25%20of%20the%20meat%20samples%20they%20tested%20were%20unsafe.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EThe%20trouble%20with%20truffles%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20likely%20culprit%20is%20the%20deer%20truffle%2C%20which%20grows%20underground%20and%20accumulates%20radioactive%20cesium.%20Wild%20boars%20root%20them%20out%2C%20especially%20during%20the%20colder%20months%20when%20other%20food%20sources%20are%20scarce.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.radioprotection.org%2Farticles%2Fradiopro%2Fabs%2F2009%2F05%2Fradiopro44108%2Fradiopro44108.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E2009%20study%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20researchers%20tested%20Bavarian%20truffles%20that%20were%20about%206%20inches%20or%20less%20underground%20and%20found%20that%20they%20were%20far%20more%20contaminated%20than%20ferns%2C%20berry%20bushes%2C%20and%20beech%20nuts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20boars'%20stomachs%20contained%20even%20a%20small%20amount%20of%20truffles%2C%20they%20were%20responsible%20for%20three-quarters%20of%20the%20radiocesium%20they%20ingested.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20though%20it's%20been%20decades%20since%20the%20tests%20and%20power%20plant%20accident%2C%20cesium%20is%20still%20slowly%20seeping%20deeper%20into%20the%20soil.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDeer%20truffles%20that%20are%20over%20a%20foot%20underground%20that%20nuclear%20weapons%20previously%20contaminated%20are%20now%20absorbing%20cesium%20from%20Chernobyl.%20In%20turn%2C%20boars%20that%20eat%20these%20truffles%20will%20accumulate%20cesium%20in%20their%20organs%20and%20tissues.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20study's%20authors%20used%20a%20gamma-ray%20detector%20to%20test%2048%20wild%20boar%20meat%20samples%20for%20cesium-137%20and%20cesium-135%20levels.%20Based%20on%20the%20ratio%20of%20the%20different%20isotopes%20of%20cesium%2C%20the%20scientists%20could%20tell%20whether%20the%20material%20was%20from%20Chernobyl%20or%20the%20older%20atmospheric%20nuclear%20weapons%20tests.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAll%20the%20affected%20meat%20samples%20had%20contamination%20from%20both%2C%20with%20the%20weapons%20contributing%20between%2010%25%20and%2068%25%20of%20the%20cesium%20in%20the%20unsafe%20boars.%20In%20about%20a%20quarter%20of%20the%20samples%2C%20the%20amount%20of%20cesium-137%20from%20weapons%20fallout%20alone%20exceeded%20the%20European%20regulatory%20limit.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BJust%20because%20they%20took%20place%2060%20years%20ago%20doesn't%20mean%20that%20they%20no%20longer%20impact%20the%20ecosystem%2C%26quot%3B%20Feng%20and%20a%20co-author%2C%20Georg%20Steinhauser%2C%20told%20the%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sciencefocus.com%2Fradioactive-boars-europe%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20BBC%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fradioactive-bavarian-boars-may-be-contaminated-by-nuclear-weapons-testing-2023-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693511342000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64efd9e3f684c600197a925a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fradioactive-bavarian-boars-may-be-contaminated-by-nuclear-weapons-testing-2023-8%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Radioactive%20Bavarian%20boars%20eat%20truffles%20contaminated%20by%20fallout%20from%20both%20Chernobyl%20and%20nuclear%20weapons%20testing%20from%20decades%20ago%2C%20a%20new%20study%20says.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22jmcgrath%40insider.com%20(Jenny%20McGrath)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A81%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fradioactive-bavarian-boars-may-be-contaminated-by-nuclear-weapons-testing-2023-8%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Javad%20Rouhi%3A%20Iranian%20protester%20dies%20in%20jail%20after%20avoiding%20death%20sentence%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693510936000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fichef.bbci.co.uk%2Fnews%2F1024%2Fbranded_news%2F1597D%2Fproduction%2F_130954488_mediaitem130939803.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-middle-east-666