n.%20Because%20in%20those%20days%2C%20when%20Trump%20could%20plausibly%20claim%20to%20be%20a%20legitimate%20government%20authority%2C%20he%20loudly%20denounced%20those%20who%20stood%20in%20his%20way%20as%20anti-democratic.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%20the%20shoe%20is%20on%20the%20other%20foot.%20Trump%20is%20out%20of%20power.%20His%20political%20prospects%20are%20clouded%20by%20four%20criminal%20indictments.%20And%20so%20Trump's%20rhetorical%20attacks%20%E2%80%94%20mindlessly%20echoed%20by%20the%20partisans%20who%20stand%20beside%20him%20and%20the%20lawyers%20who%20cash%20his%20checks%20%E2%80%94%20have%20shifted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrump's%20new%20object%20of%20hatred%20is%20the%20%3Cem%3Esurface%3C%2Fem%3E%20state%20%E2%80%94%20the%20state%20itself.%20The%20attack%20on%20the%20surface%20state%20began%2C%20of%20course%2C%20on%20January%206%2C%20when%20a%20violent%20mob%2C%20assembled%20and%20encouraged%20by%20Trump%2C%20descended%20on%20the%20Capitol%20to%20overturn%20a%20presidential%20election.%20When%20they%20weren't%20able%20to%20achieve%20that%20objective%2C%20they%20attacked%20every%20part%20of%20the%20government%20that%20they%20could%20lay%20their%20hands%20on.%20They%20trashed%20the%20floor%20of%20Congress.%20They%20punched%20and%20clawed%20at%20uniformed%20police%20officers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EToday%2C%20Trump's%20attacks%20on%20the%20surface%20state%20are%20accelerating.%20He's%20going%20after%20prosecutors%2C%20judges%2C%20grand%20juries%2C%20and%20state%20officials%20%E2%80%94%20anyone%20who%20suggests%20that%20normal%20due%20process%20move%20forward%20to%20determine%20his%20criminal%20responsibility%20for%20any%20of%20the%20above.%20He's%20called%20Special%20Counsel%20Jack%20Smith%20a%20%26quot%3Bthug%26quot%3B%20and%20a%20%26quot%3Bterrorist%2C%26quot%3B%20while%20referring%20to%20Smith's%20wife%20as%20a%20%26quot%3BTrump%20Hater.%26quot%3B%20Trump%20has%20also%20posted%20attacks%20and%20false%20allegations%20about%20Fanni%20Wills%2C%20the%20Fulton%20County%20district%20attorney.%20Since%20these%20attacks%2C%20she%20has%20reported%20receiving%20racist%20threats%20by%20email%20and%20phone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELet's%20set%20aside%20for%20a%20moment%20the%20strength%20of%20the%20evidence%20showing%20that%20Trump%20committed%20three%20sets%20of%20crimes%20%E2%80%94%20the%20January%206%20plot%2C%20absconding%20with%20classified%20documents%20to%20Mar-a-Lago%2C%20and%20the%20arm-twisting%20phone%20call%20to%20Georgia.%20Even%20if%20we%20chose%20to%20overlook%20these%20past%20actions%2C%20Trump's%20behavior%20now%20goes%20far%20beyond%20that%20of%20a%20typical%20defendant%20who%20believes%20that%20he%20has%20been%20wrongly%20accused%20and%20is%20seizing%20every%20procedural%20advantage%20to%20try%20to%20clear%20his%20name.%20Instead%2C%20he's%20making%20a%20desperate%20bid%20to%20escape%20accountability%20by%20undermining%20the%20legitimacy%20of%20the%20very%20institutions%20seeking%20to%20hold%20him%20to%20account.%20When%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.politico.com%2Fnews%2F2023%2F08%2F04%2Ffeds-alert-judge-to-trumps-if-you-go-after-me-im-coming-after-you-post-00109944%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETrump%20posted%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20Truth%20Social%20%26quot%3Bif%20you%20go%20after%20me%2C%20I'm%20coming%20after%20you%2C%26quot%3B%20there%20should%20be%20no%20doubt%20what%20the%20'you'%20refers%20to%3A%20the%20federal%2C%20state%2C%20and%20local%20governments%20of%20the%20United%20States.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Cq%3ETrump%20ultimately%20wants%20more%20than%20four%20acquittals%3B%20he%20wants%20two%20paths%20to%20winning%20an%20election.%3C%2Fq%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3Cp%3EMaybe%20Trump%20has%20forgotten%20that%20less%20than%20three%20years%20ago%2C%20he%20was%20head%20of%20the%20surface%20state.%20He%20himself%20was%20the%20person%20in%20charge%20of%20the%20Department%20of%20Justice%2C%20which%20is%20prosecuting%20two%20of%20the%20four%20cases%20against%20him.%20He%20got%20to%20pick%20two%20attorneys%20general%2C%20three%20Supreme%20Court%20justices%2C%20and%20231%20federal%20judges%2C%20including%20the%20one%20now%20overseeing%20the%20Mar-a-Lago%20documents%20case.%20It%20was%20Trump's%20official%20portrait%20hanging%20on%20the%20wall%20of%20DOJ%20headquarters%20at%20950%20Pennsylvania%20Avenue%20NW.%20So%20if%20the%20DOJ%20really%20is%20a%20cesspool%20of%20politically%20motivated%20hacks%2C%20why%20did%20Trump%20twiddle%20his%20thumbs%20for%20four%20years%20instead%20of%20cleaning%20house%3F%20Why%20didn't%20he%20declassify%20the%20secret%20documents%20that%20he%20took%20with%20him%20to%20Mar-a-Lago%3F%20Why%20didn't%20he%20accept%20the%20advice%20of%20his%20hand-picked%20White%20House%20counsel%20and%20attorney%20general%20that%20he'd%20lost%20the%20election%2C%20instead%20of%20finding%20an%20even%20more%20power-crazed%20and%20sycophantic%20gang%20of%20attorneys%20who%20would%20tell%20him%20otherwise%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20aren't%20hard%20questions.%20The%20record%20shows%20that%20Trump%20will%20say%20and%20do%20anything%20to%20feed%20his%20appetite%20for%20absolute%20power.%20The%20words%20that%20he%20says%20in%20public%20shouldn't%20really%20be%20understood%20as%20factual%20claims%20that%2C%20strung%20together%2C%20form%20coherent%20arguments.%20They're%20something%20closer%20to%20a%20special%20genre%20of%20music%2C%20intended%20for%20the%2035%25%20of%20Americans%20who%20long%20ago%20stopped%20caring%20if%20the%20lyrics%20made%20any%20sense.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20something%20has%20indeed%20changed.%20It's%20one%20thing%20to%20whip%20up%20partisan%20paranoia%20about%20the%20leadership%20and%20intentions%20of%20the%20CIA%2C%20FBI%2C%20and%20NSA%20%E2%80%94%20many%20of%20whom%20were%20indeed%20Trump's%20antagonists%2C%20particularly%20after%20he%20called%20them%20%26quot%3Bgestapo.%26quot%3B%20Any%20thinking%20person%20should%20harbor%20some%20suspicion%20of%20these%20agencies%2C%20which%20operate%20according%20to%20secret%20rules%20and%20minimal%20public%20oversight.%20It's%20another%20thing%20entirely%20to%20undermine%20America's%20faith%20in%20the%20justice%20system%20itself%20%E2%80%94%20the%20power%20of%20individual%20states%2C%20like%20Georgia%20and%20New%20York%2C%20to%20investigate%20violations%20of%20their%20own%20laws%2C%20written%20by%20elected%20officials%2C%20and%20then%20bring%20potential%20wrongdoers%20to%20justice.%20This%20is%20exactly%20what%20Trump%20is%20trying%20to%20do%20when%20he%20calls%20the%20US%20a%20%26quot%3Bbanana%20republic%26quot%3B%20with%20a%20justice%20system%20comparable%20to%20the%20%26quot%3Bthird%20world.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20defendants%20who%2C%20like%20Trump%2C%20attempt%20to%20sabotage%20the%20integrity%20of%20the%20justice%20system%20are%20entitled%20to%20the%20same%20due%20process%20and%20protections%20under%20US%20law.%20That's%20not%20a%20weakness%20of%20our%20system%3B%20it's%20a%20strength.%20Of%20course%2C%20the%20courts%20may%20find%20that%20Trump%20is%20not%20guilty.%20If%20that%20happens%2C%20his%20opponents%20should%20not%20do%20as%20Trump%20did%20with%20Hillary%20Clinton%2C%20who%20was%20never%20indicted.%20They%20should%20not%20cheer%20their%20surrogates%20on%20as%20they%20whip%20up%20angry%20supporters%20with%20chants%20of%20%26quot%3Block%20him%20up.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrump%20ultimately%20wants%20more%20than%20four%20acquittals%3B%20he%20wants%20two%20paths%20to%20winning%20an%20election.%20There's%20the%20normal%20path%2C%20winning%20the%20most%20electoral%20votes.%20Then%20there's%20the%20Trump-only%20path%2C%20refusing%20to%20take%20the%20loss%20and%20then%20illegally%20subverting%20the%20result.%20And%20if%20Trump%20chooses%20the%20%26quot%3Billegally%20subvert%26quot%3B%20path%20and%20fails%20to%20succeed%2C%20he%20doesn't%20want%20any%20courts%20to%20be%20empowered%20to%20investigate%20or%20punish%20the%20wrongdoers%20who%20enabled%20his%20attempt.%20Instead%2C%20he%20wants%20the%20unimpeded%20ability%20to%20do%20it%20all%20over%20again.%20If%20he%20succeeds%2C%20the%20result%20would%20be%20a%20political%20system%20where%20the%20minority%20can%20violently%20challenge%20the%20elected%20government%20over%20and%20over%20again%2C%20with%20no%20consequences%2C%20until%20they%20succeed%2C%20and%20then%20use%20the%20pardon%20power%20to%20print%20stacks%20of%20get-out-of-jail-free%20cards.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20sheer%20audacity%20here%20is%20absurd.%20It%20goes%20way%20beyond%20%26quot%3Bworking%20the%20refs.%26quot%3B%20It's%20more%20like%20hiring%20an%20electrician%20to%20covertly%20rewire%20the%20scoreboard%2C%20then%20taking%20a%20bazooka%20to%20the%20scoreboard%20when%20that%20effort%20fails%2C%20and%20then%20insisting%2C%20against%20mountains%20of%20evidence%2C%20that%20no%20one%20knows%20what%20the%20score%20actually%20was%2C%20so%20the%20game%20has%20to%20be%20played%20again%20and%20again%20until%20the%20losing%20team%20wins.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Cq%3EThere%20is%20no%20reason%20that%20those%20who%20continue%20to%20echo%20Trump's%20cynical%20blather%20at%20this%20late%20date%20should%20be%20taken%20seriously%20again.%20They%20should%20leave%20politics.%3C%2Fq%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20arguments%20being%20made%20by%20Trump's%20camp%20today%20are%20so%20stupid%20and%20so%20cynical%20that%20they%20can%20seem%20to%20diminish%20anyone%20who%20takes%20them%20seriously%2C%20let%20alone%20those%20who%20are%20making%20them.%20But%20they%20must%20be%20addressed%2C%20because%20Trump%20is%20not%20the%20only%20one%20making%20them%20with%20a%20straight%20face.%20These%20last%20few%20days%2C%20a%20state%20court%20in%20Georgia%20heard%20Mark%20Meadows%20insist%20that%20pressuring%20the%20Georgia%20secretary%20of%20state%20to%20find%20non-existent%20Trump%20votes%20was%20part%20of%20his%20official%20duties%20as%20the%20White%20House%20chief%20of%20staff.%20And%20a%20national%20audience%20saw%20seven%20GOP%20primary%20candidates%20raise%20their%20hands%20to%20indicate%20they'd%20support%20Trump's%20presidential%20bid%2C%20even%20if%20he%20were%20convicted%20of%20a%20felony.%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20way%20past%20time%20to%20draw%20some%20red%20lines.%20One%20place%20to%20start%20is%20the%20eight%20Republican%20senators%20who%20voted%20against%20certifying%20the%202020%20electoral%20votes%2C%20even%20%3Cem%3Eafter%20%3C%2Fem%3Ethe%20armed%20mob%20attacked%20the%20Capitol%3A%20Josh%20Hawley%2C%20Ted%20Cruz%2C%20Tommy%20Tuberville%2C%20Cindy%20Hyde-Smith%2C%20Roger%20Marshall%2C%20and%20John%20Kennedy.%20Two%20weeks%20after%20January%206%2C%20a%20group%20of%20senators%20filed%20an%20ethics%20complaint%20against%20Cruz%20and%20Hawley.%20Both%20didn't%20just%20vote%20against%20certification.%20They%20helped%20whip%20up%20the%20mob%20and%20fundraised%20off%20of%20Trump's%20baseless%20challenge.%20We've%20heard%20nothing%20from%20the%20Senate%20Ethics%20Committee%20since%20that%20complaint%20was%20filed.%20A%20spokesperson%20for%20the%20committee%20didn't%20immediately%20reply%20to%20an%20email%20asking%20if%20the%20matter%20was%20ongoing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20Senate%20is%20too%20spineless%20to%20draw%20those%20red%20lines%2C%20others%20will%20have%20to%20step%20up.%20It's%20reasonable%20for%20the%20GOP%20to%20say%20that%20Trump%20deserves%20the%20presumption%20of%20innocence%2C%20and%20that%20the%20courts%20will%20acquit%20him.%20But%20to%20suggest%20that%20it%20doesn't%20matter%20if%20he's%20guilty%20because%20the%20judicial%20deck%20is%20stacked%20is%20not%20reasonable.%20It's%20dangerous.%20The%20names%20of%20those%20who%20say%20that%20should%20be%20remembered%20in%20infamy.%20Of%20course%20this%20didn't%20happen%20with%20those%20who%20boosted%20the%20Iraq%20war%2C%20or%20with%20those%20who%20backed%20Trump%20the%20first%20time.%20But%20maybe%20it%20could%20happen%20now.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20stand%20with%20Trump%20as%20he%20openly%20attacks%20the%20justice%20system%20isn't%20only%20crazy%20and%20desperate%2C%20it's%20also%20arguably%20short-sighted%2C%20a%20reflex%20by%20loyalist%20hacks%20who%20can't%20see%20that%20there%20is%20no%20longer%20much%20of%20a%20political%20upside.%20Trump%20is%20old.%20He%20will%20not%20be%20the%20dominant%20GOP%20figure%20forever%3B%20there%20is%20no%20reason%20that%20those%20who%20continue%20to%20echo%20his%20cynical%20blather%20at%20this%20late%20date%20should%20be%20taken%20seriously%20again.%20They%20should%20leave%20politics.%20They%20should%20be%20shunned%20by%20the%20normal%20Beltway%20retirement%20communities%E2%80%94the%20think%20tanks%2C%20the%20lobbying%20groups%2C%20and%20the%20cable%20news%20shows.%20Serious%20people%20should%20refuse%20to%20meet%20with%20them.%20The%20lawyers%20among%20them%20should%20be%20disbarred.%20They%20should%20try%20their%20hands%20at%20some%20honorable%20work%20instead%20of%20lying%20for%20a%20living.%20They%20should%20get%20jobs%20at%20Trader%20Joe's.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Fmattathias-schwartz%5C%22%3EMattathias%20Schwartz%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20chief%20national%20security%20correspondent%20at%20Insider.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdeep-state-trump-war-government-justice-indictments-2023-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693506541000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64f0d07557bff7001947bb34%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdeep-state-trump-war-government-justice-indictments-2023-8%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Trump's%20attacks%20have%20entered%20a%20dangerous%20new%20phase%2C%20seeking%20to%20delegitimize%20not%20just%20the%20%26quot%3Bdeep%20state%26quot%3B%20but%20the%20idea%20of%20legitimate%20government%20itself.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22mschwartz%40businessinsider.com%20(Mattathias%20Schwartz)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A196%2C%22canonica