ending-delinquencies-student-debt-2023-8%5C%22%3Ehas%20been%20hanging%20strong%20so%20far%20this%20year%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20spending%20still%20rising%20and%20on%20track%20to%20drive%20third-quarter%20GDP%20growth%20of%20up%20to%203.5%25%2C%20according%20to%20a%20Thursday%20note%20from%20ING%20Economics.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20spending%20habits%20are%20unsustainable%2C%20and%20a%20decline%20in%20consumer%20spending%20is%20likely%20coming%20in%20early%202024%2C%20according%20to%20the%20note.%20That's%20because%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fconsumer-credit-card-debt-tops-1-trillion-first-time-ever-2023-8%5C%22%3Ecredit%20card%20debts%20are%20piling%20up%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20excess%20savings%20from%20the%20pandemic%20are%20being%20depleted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20problem%20is%20savings%20are%20finite%20and%20the%20banks%20are%20tightening%20lending%20standards%20significantly.%20Credit%20card%20borrowing%20costs%20are%20the%20highest%20since%20records%20began%20in%201972%20so%20there%20is%20going%20to%20be%20a%20lot%20of%20pain%20out%20there%2C%26quot%3B%20ING's%20chief%20international%20economist%20James%20Knightley%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20while%20a%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcategory%2Fjob-market%5C%22%3Esolid%20jobs%20market%20provides%20a%20strong%20base%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20consumers%20to%20keep%20spending%2C%20wage%20growth%20has%20been%20tracking%20below%20inflation%2C%20and%20savings%20trends%20have%20been%20deteriorating.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20have%20seen%20savings%20flows%20reverse%20and%20now%20we%20are%20running%20them%20down%20each%20and%20every%20month%2C%20which%20is%20not%20sustainable%20over%20the%20long%20term%2C%26quot%3B%20Knightley%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20estimated%20that%20at%20the%20current%20rate%20of%20spending%2C%20excess%20savings%20from%20the%20pandemic%20will%20be%20fully%20exhausted%20by%20the%20second%20quarter%20of%202024%2C%20and%20even%20