sits-another-rs-100-cr-in-jet-airways-under-its-revival-plan-123083101358_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Article%20370%3A%20SC%20Asked%20to%20Consider%20It%20a%20Political%20Compromise%20and%20Not%20Search%20For%20Logic%20in%20It%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F31224356%2FSupreme-Court-II-png.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20language%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ftag%2Farticle-370%5C%22%3EArticle%20370%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%93%20the%20reading%20down%20of%20which%20by%20parliament%20is%20under%20challenge%20before%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20%E2%80%93%20continued%20to%20engage%20the%20attention%20of%20the%20bench%20and%20the%20senior%20counsel%20on%20the%2013th%20day%20of%20hearing%20before%20the%20five-judge%20constitution%20bench%20on%20Thursday%20(August%2031).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESenior%20advocate%20Rakesh%20Dwivedi%20reasoned%20that%20Article%20370%20has%20outlived%20its%20utility%20and%20that%20the%20President%E2%80%99s%20decision%20as%20a%20constituent%20body%20under%20Article%20370(3)%20should%20not%20be%20questioned.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%20D.Y.%20Chandrachud%20sought%20to%20link%20the%20continued%20existence%20of%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20(J%26amp%3BK)%20as%20a%20state%20to%20Indian%20federalism.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEarlier%2C%20the%20bench%20took%20note%20of%20senior%20counsel%20Kapil%20Sibal%E2%80%99s%20submission%20that%20it%20should%20not%20consider%20the%20Union%20government%E2%80%99s%20extraneous%20claims%20with%20regard%20to%20the%20restoration%20of%20J%26amp%3BK%E2%80%99s%20statehood%20while%20deciding%20the%20challenges%20to%20its%20conversion%20into%20a%20union%20territory.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20second%20day%2C%20the%20Union%20government%20refused%20to%20indicate%20a%20time%20frame%20for%20restoring%20J%26amp%3BK%E2%80%99s%20statehood%2C%20even%20as%20the%20bench%20made%20it%20clear%20that%20it%20would%20consider%20only%20the%20constitutional%20grounds%20while%20adjudicating%20the%20challenges%20before%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDwivedi%20argued%20that%20the%20doctrine%20of%20presumption%20of%20validity%20of%20laws%20passed%20by%20parliament%20requires%20the%20petitioners%20to%20rebut%20it.%20%E2%80%9CIf%20two%20views%20are%20possible%2C%20then%20the%20one%20which%20sustains%20the%20exercise%20of%20power%20has%20to%20be%20preferred%E2%80%9D%2C%20he%20told%20the%20bench.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESenior%20counsel%20Harish%20Salve%20said%20that%20a%20law%20cannot%20be%20held%20to%20violate%20of%20the%20basic%20structure%20of%20the%20constitution%20and%20that%20only%20constitutional%20amendments%20can%20be%20challenged%20on%20that%20ground.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20reading%20down%20of%20Article%20370%20must%20be%20construed%20as%20aimed%20at%20protecting%20civil%20liberties%2C%20and%20it%20should%20therefore%20be%20seen%20as%20being%20aligned%20with%20the%20basic%20structure%2C%20Salve%20claimed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETaking%20the%20bench%20through%20the%20language%20adopted%20in%20Article%20370%2C%20Salve%20said%20Article%20370(3)%20uses%20the%20word%20%E2%80%98recommendation%E2%80%99%20instead%20of%20%E2%80%98concurrence%E2%80%99%2C%20and%20therefore%2C%20by%20reserving%20the%20power%20to%20the%20president%20to%20make%20it%20inoperative%2C%20there%20cannot%20be%20concurrence%20of%20the%20constituent%20assembly%2C%20which%20is%20no%20longer%20in%20existence%2C%20he%20explained.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20Read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhistory%2Fpublic-first-time-jammu-kashmirs-instrument-accession-india%5C%22%3EThe%20Backstory%20of%20Article%20370%3A%20A%20True%20Copy%20of%20J%26amp%3BK%E2%80%99s%20Instrument%20of%20Accession%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBy%20making%20it%20clear%20that%20only%20consultation%20(rather%20than%20concurrence)%20was%20required%20if%20the%20president%20wanted%20to%20make%20any%20exception%20or%20modification%20concerning%20defence%2C%20security%20and%20foreign%20affairs%20(subjects%20mentioned%20in%20Instrument%20of%20Accession%20(IoA))%2C%20Article%20370%20made%20the%20constitution-framers%E2%80%99%20intentions%20clear%2C%20Salve%20suggested%2C%20and%20asked%20the%20bench%20to%20ponder%20over%20why%20they%20used%20different%20words%20in%20different%20contexts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThere%20was%20a%20political%20compromise%20and%20the%20accession%20was%20complete%3B%20Article%20370(3)%20was%20aimed%20to%20put%20an%20end%20to%20the%20political%20compromise%E2%80%9D%2C%20Salve%20told%20the%20bench.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20Bench%20asked%20Salve%20whether%20the%20abrogation%20of%20the%20provision%20itself%20%E2%80%93%20which%20has%20a%20greater%20constitutional%20impact%20than%20exceptions%20and%20modifications%20of%20the%20Article%20%E2%80%93%20could%20have%20been%20conceived%20by%20the%20constitution-framers%20as%20not%20meriting%20the%20restriction%20of%20consultation%20and%20concurrence%20(as%20opposed%20to%20mere%20recommendation%2C%20which%20is%20not%20binding).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20this%2C%20Salve%20claimed%20Article%20370%20was%20a%20unique%20provision%20that%20left%20the%20last%20word%20to%20the%20Union%20government%20when%20it%20came%20to%20the%20IoA.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETherefore%2C%20he%20submitted%2C%20this%20dichotomy%20was%20built-in.%20According%20to%20him%2C%20one%20cannot%20search%20for%20too%20much%20logic%20in%20this%20provision%2C%20and%20as%20a%20political%20clause%2C%20the%20court%20must%20give%20it%20the%20widest%20meaning%20possible.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDissecting%20the%20language%20of%20Article%20370%2C%20Salve%20suggested%20that%20the%20president%20could%20have%20got%20a%20recommendation%20from%20the%20state%20constituent%20assembly%20if%20it%20existed.%20The%20president%20does%20not%20lose%20her%20power%20if%20there%20is%20a%20vacuum%2C%20he%20contended.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEarlier%2C%20attorney%20general%20(AG)%20R.%20Venkataramani%20submitted%20that%20the%20determination%20of%20Article%20370%20must%20occur%20at%20some%20time%20and%20that%20the%20president%20could%20not%20be%20excluded%20from%20doing%20so%20now.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EResponding%20to%20the%20chief%20justice%E2%80%99s%20view%20that%20ends%20cannot%20justify%20the%20means%2C%20the%20AG%20said%20J%26amp%3BK%20provided%20a%20complex%20situation%20and%20that%20there%20is%20no%20mathematical%20formula%20to%20address%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693502216000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F31224356%2FSupreme-Court-II-png.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsc-asked-to-consider-article-370-a-political-compromise%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%20D.Y.%20Chandrachud%20underlined%20that%20the%20continued%20existence%20of%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20as%20a%20state%20is%20integral%20to%20Indian%20federalism.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsc-asked-to-consider-article-370-a-political-compromise%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Govt%20invites%20Expression%20of%20Interest%20from%20bidders%20for%20IMPCL%20strategic%20sale%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693500459000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fimg%2Farticle%2F2020-01%2F08%2Ffull%2F1578422279-9627.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fgovt-invites-expression-of-interests-for-impcl-strategic-disinvestment-123083101113_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20turnover%20of%20the%20company%20rose%20by%2059%20per%20cent%20to%20Rs%20261%20crore%20in%20FY22.%20Its%20profit%20after%20tax%20stood%20at%20Rs%2034%20crore%20for%202021-22%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22cano